description: Start just left of Yabadabadoo. Move up and left into the bomber hand crack. Awkward top out. (Originally a sit start, but the start hold broke off. Sit start is much harder now.)

name: Twinkle toes
description: Start with a right hand in the crack and left hand crimping the small diagonal crack. Move straight over the techy slab using small crimps.

name: Wilma’s way
description: Fun little shorty on the same boulder as Flontstoned.

name: Yabadabadoo!
description: Sit start on a low jug (same as Pebbles), but move right up to very cool dog bone feature. Very fun movement!

name: Cherry jam
description: Juggy variation

name: Cherry Poppin
description: Fun easy face climbing.

name: Just friends
description: Slopey crimpy slab

name: Peanut Butter and Jam
description: Awesome hand jams!

name: Rubber Duckie
description: Sit start in a hand crack. Climb up and left, over the detached boulder.

name: Flapper Vision
description: Start on an obvious jug.

name: No Protection
description: Cross-pressure in a chimney then mantle onto a flake.

name: Propane In a Blender
description: Climb up the arete then traverse left into crack to top out.

name: Steve Irwin
description: Grunt up a small chimney to a weird top out.

name: Booger
description: Climb the right side of the Big Nose.

name: Scent of a Man
description: Steepest highest line on the Big Nose

name: Sneeze
description: Fun face climb on the right side of the Big Nose.

name: Snot rocket
description: Start on a jug on left side of the boulder. Work straight up the slab.

name: Snot Rocket sit
description: Sit start under the nose and move left into Snot Rocket.

name: Rack em up
description: Follow the diagonal crack up and right.

name: Scratch
description: Start on a couple crimps and mantle up.

name: Slop counts
description: Traverse the lip of the large crack.

name: Gothmog Lean
description: Hands on the lump, run up the front of the boulder. Balancy with some nice heel rocking

name: 3 Amigos
description: Yet another good warmup.

name: Cabezas de Pollo
description: Easy knobs!

name: Chevy Chase
description: Another fun easy line.

name: Chicken out
description: Start on opposing gastons, move up and chicken out right before the top.

name: Mini Fridge
description: Hug the mini fridge. No dabs on surrounding rocks.

name: Monkey Bars
description: Easy but steep.

name: Pout Pout Fish
description: Easy line up the right side of the face.

name: Teeter Totter
description: Fun easy line.

name: Fake News
description: Start on a good jug with a good foot. Make an easy press move to the slab above.

name: French Press
description: Start on high crimps. Pull up and press it out.

name: Read all about it
description: Sit start with awkward feet and press up into the slab.

name: Damn Slab
description: High ball featured slab climbing

name: Soup or Solid
description: Traverse the lip moving right.

name: Struggle bus
description: Crimp the steep face. Go straight up.

name: Dab if you do, damned if you don’t
description: Obvious arete on the Volcom boulder.

name: Q traverse
description: Traverse the slabby lip of the small boulder directly next to the Volcom.

name: Volcom chimney
description: Fun little squeeze.

name: Volcom slab
description: Slab your way to the top of the Volcom.

name: Everlasting Gobstopper traverse
description: Traverse left (recommended) or right all the way around the boulder starting and finishing on the large gobstopper jug. Mantle top out from the big gobstopper.

name: Fun Dip
description: Climb up over the horizontal crack on knobs.

name: Gobstopper
description: Variation of Wonka bar. Stay left avoiding the juggy flake used to top out Wonka bar. Finish on the giant gobstopper jug instead. Pull hard and mantle out. A bit contrived, but a good variation.

name: Gumballs
description: Anoth fun knobby slab.

name: Laffy Taffy
description: Easy slab climb

name: Pixy Stix
description: Yet another fun easy slab climb.

name: Runts
description: Easy knobs.

name: Sticky fingers
description: Sit start on the right side of the roof. Pull up and over the slabby bulge.

name: Sweet Tarts
description: Another easy slab going up to the right of Laffy Taffy.

name: Wonka bar
description: Climb out from under the roof on good holds.

name: 3 Bar
description: An easy warm-up climb before you get to the higher boulders. Easy exit off the back.

name: Dad bod
description: Starting from a sit start, move up and to the left to eventually top out. The rock is of good quality on this climb. This one of two climbs on the south side of the boulder. Looking at the south side, it is furthest to the left.

name: Lazy Bum
description: Fun little climb. Could be modified for a sit start but it would be much harder. There are two ledges that work as good handholds for a standing start with feet on the smaller boulder below.Some of the rock on this route is pretty rotten but it's been cleaned pretty good. Be prepared for loose rocks.This climb is the second on the south side of the boulder. Looking at the south side, it is far to the right following a crack.

name: Donut Hole
description: Fun and different. This climb goes up both the west and east sides of the Boulder and ends at the top. Starting on the west face, the climbers climbs up into the hole, across it, and then out, up the east face.

name: El Zoro
description: Straight up and exit to your left. Good rock but a little mossy.

name: Foot Fungus
description: You start at the left side of the east face, to the right of the hole. Simply follow the crack to the top.

name: Momma's Boy
description: Flat landing and straight up the boulder. Good Rock.

name: Dead Bird
description: This Highball boulder is pretty fun as long as you don't mind the heights. A sit start could be implemented.

name: RIP Pants
description: Trying to only use the boulders on the right, this climb is pretty fun as you reach to the very top looking for that nice hold. You could climb to the top of the boulder and walk around it to exit but I find it easiest just to down climb and jump.

name: One in the Hand
description: Starting at the bottom of the right crack on the east side, follow it up and finish to the right rather than the left.

name: Two in The Bush
description: Great rock but the landing requires at least one great spotter and a crashpad. Pretty fun spot.

name: Camel's Back
description: As soon as you get up the first 10 feet, it's not as hard.

name: Little Ninja
description: The reason for the higher rating is because it's so difficult for taller people to complete. The only person to complete it so far is an American Ninja Warrior competitor, Lance Pekus.

name: Little Peña
description: The route is pretty simple. Follow up and exit out back.

name: Long Boy
description: Standing Start. I'm 5'9 and started standing on 2 crash pads for the starting holds but you can start lower, it just makes it a little harder.

name: Thick-Neck
description: It doesn't get much simpler than this one. Just go straight up anywhere you can.

name: Crash'N Crunch
description: The landing isn't flat but as long as you have a good spotter you'll be fine. This climb is a topout and exit off the back or sides.

name: Loose Ledge
description: It's a pretty fun little climb that ends as soon as you reach your hand over to the top. If you go up and over, that's a different climb at about a V3.

name: Wobble Rock
description: Wobble Rock gets its name from the Rock on the top that isn't attached. It's a pretty fun little climb that ends as soon as you top out. If you don't want to go up and over, that's a different climb at about a V1-V2.

name: [Redacted]
description: Climb about twenty feet up on easy, clean rock to the first bolt. A cam is available before clipping this. Step right and up past some kinda thin slab by moves past two more bolts and green camalot in a slot above third bolt. Move up to an anchor and either belay here or clip it long and move right to the continuation up a clean orange arête. Two more bolts to a two bolt anchor. One long rap with a 70 or if not sure use intermediate anchor to get down.

name: [Redacted]
description: This is the route previously known as chicks and ticks. I finally got around to putting a couple bolts in it and is a fun lead.

name: Big girl panties
description: This route starts by climbing two bit whore to the intermediate anchor. It is better to belay here for drag. Climb up and left above anchor, good cam, then onto arête and a bolt. Pull around left and follow slab/ arête past a large block forming an under cling, bolt. Move up and left to top of flake and steep bulge, bolt. Launch out left on obvious white flake till you can pull around to good stance and bolt. Did you have your big girl panties on? Go straight up to anchor, rap route.

name: Blue steel arete
description: This climbs the obvious sharp arête to the left of two bit whore. Fun balancy moves up the arête to anchor. Watch for a little loose block about half way up. Tried to get it out many times!

name: Boys don't cry
description: The first pitch climbs the obvious arete to the right of great wide open. Clip a bolt and make some slabby moves up to a diagonal crack with good nut pro. Continue up the arete past three more bolts and some gear to a 2BB on a good ledge. 30m, 5.8.    P2 Continue up the arete past a bolt , over a bulge with good pro and into the shallow corner system on the right, fixed pin, some gear then another bolt. Make harder moves stemming and smearing up the corner, good gear to 3" then a 2BB at another good ledge. 30m, 5.9+. Great pitch.   The route will probably continue past this pitch but hasn't been done yet.

name: Great wide open
description: This climb is on a different section further left as you look at the crag. Hike up the scree slope to the center of the compact grey slab. P1 starts in a sea below a bolt, straight up past three bolts and gear to number 1 Camelot. 2 BB. 5.8.30m   P2 heads up and left through two roof lines to gain a dished slab with a shallow corner in the middle. Five bolts, a pin and small cams up to a .75. Very nice pitch pulling through roofs, great moves. Ends at a 2 BB at an awesome ledge. 5.8+30m   P3 climbs directly above belay following seams and a couple easy bulges to a 2 BB , gear to 2 Camelot. 5.7 30 m.

name: Magnum face
description: This climbs  the face to the left of blue steel. Move up flakes and cracks to a pin below a bulge, thin moves through this onto some sustained edging above and a little spaced gear. Continuous climbing up and right and to the right facing flake below and left of blue steel anchors.

name: One eyed trouser snake
description: This route has now been straightened out with a direct start. Start at the bottom of the large corner system to the right of snakes and ladders. Climb slab to left but use corner for pro up to 4". Move left to a bulge, small cam in a horizontal protects some slabby moves to a ledge and bolt, continue up to original bolt then follow flakes and main corner with good cams to 2".  Clip a pin and make crux moves over smooth stone, then more cams protect the last moves to a semi hanging belay. 2BB. Rap off chains single 60m rope.

name: Slippery snake
description: This climbs the face left of snake eyes.first climb some easy cracks with gear to where the slab gets compact and steepens. Bolt then balancy moves straight up to a good #2camalot and foot stance below crux and another bolt. Thin smears follow to a shallow flake and a good piece  of gear in a slot. Follow the crack up and right past more gear to the snake eyes anchor

name: Snake eyes
description: The other obvious arête left of blue steel. Great rock with a feisty crux at the obvious dogleg in arête about a third of the way up. Thin moves past this to a good finger crack and a cam. Continue up past a couple more bolts to top.

name: Snakes and ladders
description: First route climbed at slabs, nice outing up a flake that dog legs up the slab. Climb flake to anchor. Nice moves lay backing and a mantle to top.

name: Tick in the taint
description: A good slab left of great wide open.

name: You Should See the Horses
description: Mixed route.  Follow three black bolts to chains.  There are a variety of cracks down lower that take good cam placements, up to #1 C4.  There is a mini-crux right before the last bolt that can seem a little tenuous.  A bomber nut up and left will protect the move (something like a BD 7). Clip the last bolt and mantle to the chains (crux).

name: Aftershocks and Afterthoughts
description: Follow the slanting groove up and over towards the right arête before moving back left to the shallow crack leading to a series of small undercling roofs. After arriving at the last and largest roof there are two variations.Move left for easier glory climbing on the 'Aftershocks' variation (gear, ~11c).For a little more challenge and exposure, climb the 'Afterthoughts' variation by moving right towards a pair of chicken heads and clipping a single bolt. Enjoy a no hands rest standing on the chicken heads and resist the urge to clip the bolt of Tower Block Neurosis around the corner. Stay on the face and use a crimp in the seam to the left to enter a final sequence finishing with a slap to good edge followed by jugs to the top. Might bump the grade closer to 11d.Rap the route.

name: Bodie was a bad man
description: This is the companion route to make it two Utah....follow the same approach, rap the pillar but climb the left/ upstream side. Slightly harder than the other route.

name: Gas leak
description: This route is on the blocky slab at the bottom right of the area, known as the road kill tower. See accompanying map. This wall faces down stream and offers great afternoon shade on a hot summers day. Start at center of wall below obvious right trending twin cracks. Awkward face climbing past three bolts leads you to the crack system. Climb flared jams up and right to a two bolt anchor below the small tree.

name: High rise heist
description: This route climbs flakes and cracks diagonally right up the right side of the penthouse. Either start ground level via some flared cracks to an obvious ledge(not well protected) or scramble directly on to the ledge from the gully on right. A good belay can be set here. Climb the steep left arching flake(crux) into the crack system above. Awkward climbing follows up the cracks, good gear available but sometimes not obvious. Be aware of the loose flake about half way up. After the tree step right onto easy terrain to the two bolt belay.

name: Make it two Utah
description: This fine little arête is on the point break pillar. From the trail at the penthouse head through the saddle and to the right. You will see the top of the formation, scramble carefully over to the top, making an exposed move to the anchors which face out over the highway. You can easily short rope to this anchor. Rap down the route and climb it back to anchor. Alternatively you can scramble up a steep loose gully from below to base of route, not recommended.

name: Penthouse sweet
description: This fine outing climbs the main face ( facing highway)of the penthouse pillar. Start just right of center below some cracks. Clip a bolt and move up a short face, clip another bolt then into the crack, good #2/3 camalot here. A long sling is advisable then move left out through the bulge, bolt , and onto the face above. Move left and up, bolt, pass a flake on right then up,to under cling flake and another bolt. Move left slightly to base of crack, then up it with a couple good small to medium pieces. The crack fads out onto the blunt, slabby arête above. Make sustained, thin ,smeary moves up this past two bolts then the anchor....yahoo!

name: Rats in the belfry
description: This chimney behind the penthouse leads to a notch from where you can hit the summit of the penthouse or the rooftop. Classic chimney with a crux at a bulge to the notch. An anchor can be made here then either step out across the wall and up onto a short slab, gear then run it out to the summit of the rooftop.....or step across and up onto the summit of the penthouse where you will find a two bolt belay.

name: Road kill
description: This is the right side of gas leak. Start up gas leak, clip first two bolts, put a long sling on the second bolt. Move right along a finger traverse to a good two finger pocket and a bolt. Climb sustained thin slab past three more bolts to a two bolt anchor. Great climb.

name: Slap Happy
description: Sharp arete with 3 bolts leads to a corner with small to medium cams. Bolt anchor on top. It is possible to hike up and around to anchors if you don’t want to lead. Slightly contrived at bottom where it is possible to avoid the starting moves by stemming into scrubby corner....don’t! Technical and thin arete with 3 bolts to a big ledge. A horizontal takes a good number 1 cam and the corner has finger and smaller sizes. Double bolt anchor on top.

name: Tick Magnet
description: Fun steep climbing on good holds. Start off ledge onto some horizontals to first bolt. Crux is a reach to a good finger crack between first and second bolt. Then up and left across nice flake, two more bolts here then pull around onto slabby ramp of high rise heist. Another bolt, and a long sling for tree. Use same anchor as high rise heist.

name: Butt-dial From Satan
description: Starts with pulling a roof (stick clip the second bolt? I did). This however is not the crux. Commence up a vertical face with many sloping crips and bad feet with the occasional side pull. (Seems to collect a bit of dirt and cat litter...which detracted from the routes overall experience) None the less the roof was exciting and the face is very aesthetic.

name: Feeling Frisky
description: Fun moves up a dihedral. Crux seemed to be getting off the ground and established into the corner.

name: Kind Veggie Brother
description: Fun slab moves up to a tiny roof feature where you'll find a very satisfying undercling to latch onto. Move past the last two bolts on small, but positive holds (crux). Look for anchor up and to the right.  Originally rated 5.11a/b

name: Little Bear Hug
description: Well-protected sport climb with fun moves up the left side of the wall.

name: Rusty Knife
description: Fun moves as you climb using both the arete down low and then transitioning into the vertical seams on the face following the line of bolts.

name: You Be Lichen It
description: A tricky start leads you into a small left-facing dihedral. Continue up to a small roof feature and undercling your way left while smearing your feet until it's possible to latch onto a very positive sidepull. Continue straight up to anchors.

name: Esoteric
description: One of the finest routes in Southeast Idaho, Esoteric is long, steep, and action-packed from ground to chains. Start in the obvious gray streak, stem up between columns, and into the cave. Save some energy! The finish is a series of dynamic throws on big holds requiring power and plenty of endurance. An area classic, for sure. 60 meter rope necessary.

name: Naiad
description: Another very fun route with movement unlike that found at the other crags along the South Fork corridor. Naiad and Proboscis start together and diverge at the fifth bolt. Navigate a series of steep bulges on positive holds to an excellent rest. Don't celebrate too soon--the business is at the top!

name: Proboscis
description: The crux is in the final half, so take it easy as you stem your way up between the columns. At the fifth bolt, continue up (Naiad trends right) into steeper terrain. Keep it together--the final half requires a good combination of power and endurance.

name: Bitty
description: Once upon a time, this was the warm-up, but it always felt stout to me (12a/b). Legend has it, the correct beta brings it into the 11 range. Don't blow it when clipping--you'll deck.

name: Margin Walker
description: Smack dab in the cave’s steepest terrain. Big moves and powerful body tension lead to the head wall, where you merge with Esoteric for the final few bolts on smaller, positive holds.

name: Occult
description: Not quite as steep as Margin Walker (but pretty darn close!), Occult is another route requiring nearly horizontal big moves and a seriously attentive core.  Presently, Occult has no final anchors. Install some—or just lower from the final bolt.

name: Badger
description: Powerful upward-sloping traverse on sharp holds to a tricky top out

name: Black Skimmer
description: Start on great pockets under the roof, throw for the huge rail, work right then up

name: Galileo
description: This is a great route with super positive holds that hits some of the best parts of the outer cave.  Haven't done the direct finish over the top (would basically be a no-feet mantle).  I imagine that would be more like v3 or 4 and you'd want a spotter.  Start with right hand in the wide crack on a good flake.  Head up the crack to a big jug under the roof.  Reach to a great pocket around the lip then slap the top and traverse right to top out

name: Chairs
description: Start on jug under the overhang, pull to the lip, throw for a high pocket and mantle to get on top

name: Tiger King
description: Start in the cave and reach for the seam.  Head straigh up to the lip on good holds, then follow the sloping rail left all the way around the corner until you can high step to get on top.  Feet under the roof while you traverse.  Go straight up and over the lip without traversing for "Chairs" V2 problem

name: Mesa
description: start at the south side base climb the vertical crack and traverse to the left and up and over on a great hold near the top.

name: On/Off
description: Fun slab pocket problem

name: Pocket Full of Bees
description: Start on the right (south) side of the arete with a 2-finger pocket for your right hand and a very small but good vertical crimp with your left (around the arete). Lunge for another great 2-finger pocket then work your way up and left to top out.

name: Flat Earthers
description: A fun pocket/edge face climb on the west end of the main wall of gunk bluff

name: Looking Glass
description: Start in the vertical crack and move left into deep pockets/jugs. Mantle topout

name: Happy Meal
description: Start on a great two hand jug at the lip of the roof, with bad feet below. Fire to a shallow pocket, then another. Set your feet and lunge for the shelf. Mantle and top out

name: Arch
description: Start on low undercling and make a long reach to a good jug, match and then another far reach to good finishing jug.

name: The Bloom
description: Sit start on a combination of low crimps and a pinch, work up the thin face to a big throw to the lip. Classic!

name: Butterfly Slab
description: Stand start with smears and your hands in thins seams. Make your way up the short white slab using more seams and eventually the jug arête out right, then hit the lip to summit.

name: The grotto
description: Start in the back of the cave on the sidepull an lh sloper, go to jug in middle of the roof and then long move to jugs over the lip.

name: Lakeside traverse
description: Traverse the lip from right to left. Steep with good sharp holds.

name: Slap the Dong
description: Start on chest high flat edge in the middle of the wall. Use the small crimps in the seam to gain jugs to the summit.

name: Bloomin' Onion
description: Start matched on the head high crimp rail. Make moves on small gastons and edges to gain better holds all the way to the top. Amazing movement!

name: Midnight Stroll
description: Many variations exist on this wall. The easiest/cleanest way was chosen for the topo picture.

name: Bride of Crankenstein
description: Chossy climbing to the first bolt, then brilliant horizontal moves on jugs. difficult crux pulling the lip.     Some say it's soft for the grade.

name: Drug Train
description: Either start left of the first bolt or winch start to the first bolt. Move diagonally right to crux at bolt 4. Good pockets up top.

name: El Jefe
description: Scramble through loose section to 1st bolt and jugs. Then proceed up overhang to sharp, but massive jugs. Keep powering as the route veers right and then straight up to anchors.

name: free fallin'
description: a decent warm-up for the main cave. grovel at the lip...   once the trickery is learned, it doesn't feel hard anymore.    has been done without the tram start, but it's not really worth doing.

name: The Hive
description: Bouldery start to underclings on small roof. Use crack through roof to get over roof to crimps then massive jugs. Finishes on sharp pockets with a couple of powerful moves to the anchors.    The routes name comes from a bee hive located in a pod just left of the route.

name: karma police
description: beta intensive, bouldery roof climbing. some holds have been taken over by bird nests.

name: los adalberto's especial
description: sequential and powerful, has a bolt in the very back of the cave for the belayer. merges left into karma police at the top. feels noticeably harder than everything else in the cave.    the poopy hole may need cleaned out from time to time, but if you're on this route before/after birds take up residence, it should stay clean.

name: love to burn
description: start as for 'el jefe', bust right after the crux along the rail to the hole on 'riff raff', then continue up 'riff'.    a fun link up, worth a go really.

name: Powder Finger
description: Work up small flake to big holds, lieback on positive holds to great pocketed short upper section to anchors. A very fun routejust wish it was twice as long.

name: riff raff
description: (sorry, internet was giving me grief adding route description)    found directly left of 'wave', now has a rope for the tram start. has been done from the ground, but that doesn't add much.     fixed gear. not sure if there is an anchor yet, either lower from last chain draw or walk off. stick clip.

name: soul power
description: fun, popular route. great movement.     some trickery has discovered knee pads to be useful.

name: subterranean homesick alien
description: essentially a right hand start to 'karma police'. climbs a short boulder problem then moves directly into the crux section of 'karma'. maybe not as good because it skips the fun intro to karma, but still worth doing.

name: Supernaut
description: Bouldery start onto small ledge, (stick clip first bolt). Work through somewhat funky rock to crack/seam then straight up to anchors.

name: wave of mutilation
description: easily the best route in the cave.    fun, tricky, and dynamic movement. a knee pad proved useful.     not sure if the top has been opened yet, but ending on karma police adds another cruxy move and some good pulling.

name: American Idle
description: Crimpy & slabby route.

name: Chubby Rain
description: Hard crux off the ground getting to first bolt.  A little slabby at the 3rd bolt.  Easy above that.  So-so route.

name: Deep Dark Hole
description: Technical, slabby crux to gain a small pocket.  More slabbing above.  Fun.

name: Duck, Duck, Weird Duck
description: Move up a corner feature and past two distinct cruxes, early and late. Moving right at bolt four helps. Continue up and left onto a steeper wall to the chains.

name: Five Seven
description: Awesome rock, but short. At a great hold clip the first bolt and then mantle up onto a small ledge before heading up and left to the chains.  **Couldn't find any FA info in guidebooks about this one, but it's nice.

name: Gizmo
description: Awkward start. Pull to a crimp to the right of the first bolt, clip it, and continue on slabby interesting terrain to the top. Some very cool holds throughout that push you left!

name: Happy, Happy, Happy
description: Slab and chert featured to start then bigger holds to the top. Wanders back and forth of the bolt line.

name: Hippies
description: Difficult start and finish on steep terrain.

name: Look Ma, No Hands
description: Move up and right to rest on a big flake, then left along the bolt line to chains.

name: Might As Well Jump
description: The best route I've climbed at Darby.  Doesn't look like much, but the climbing is excellent. Positive holds up steep rock characterize this climb.

name: Natural Born Swillers
description: Up and over three distinct bulges to the chains. Sustained.

name: Red Headed Step Child
description: A big pocket low gets you to the first bolt. Continue up on thin holds to the chains.

name: Rexquando
description: Tough moves to a strenuous layback.

name: Samsonite
description: No text - use the 'Improve This Page' link to add something useful!

name: Skyler's Butt
description: Follow the flake or crack or whatever you call it. Crux is right at the beginning, do a bit of smearing until you can get a good foot. Can be a little wet and mossy, especially in the cracks, so watch out for that Solid holds, fun beginner route.

name: Stemming for Dollars
description: Enjoyable climbing with an undercling crux.

name: Stripe
description: Starts on a section of steep red rock and positive holds to a huge jug where the rock turns back to grey. Stay right of the first few bolts. Easier climbing to the anchors.

name: Swedish Chest Thrust
description: Thin crux off the ground to clip the first bolt.  Interesting climbing above.

name: Velvet Elvis
description: Thuggy, fun climbing - different and more powerful than the slab climbs near by.   Crux is off the ground and clipping the first bolt.   The second bolt is oddly placed, and requires an extra move left to clip.  After that, straight up to big holds, and then left to the third bolt.  Continue straight up big holds and past another both to the anchor.

name: Wango Tango
description: Cool route.  Bouldery (and a little loose) off the ground.  The roof is easier than it looks.  Then up the engaging slab above.  Lots of sidepulls keep it interesting up top.

name: Desperado
description: Climb a column to a steep roof, then pockets on a sustained headwall.

name: The Hidden
description: A fun overhung warmup route with a lot of large holds and two sandwich ledges. A heady runout at one clip.

name: The Widowmaker
description: Named for a huge loose block at the middle of the route.

name: Born to Rock
description: Route follows a clean crimpy face with very little chance to rest.

name: The Devil in Miss Jones
description: Traverse up ramp on East wall.  Then head up and slightly right continuing over bulge and on to the chains.  Fun

name: Rock-A-Bye Baby
description: Rock-A-Bye Baby is by far the most popular route on the crag mainly because it is easy and stands out from other climbs.  Follow arete/chimney through jugs and pockets. Things get a bit slick and crimpy right before the roof.  The crux is either the obvious roof two-thirds the way up or the first 15 ft of the climb.  You can get over the roof by pulling into a large undercling and reaching over for hidden jugs.  Be careful using the undercling as it seems a bit loose.  Possibly an easier way over the roof is to use the crack 3 feet to the right.  Due to the polished rock from all the traffic, this route is tricky for the first few bolts, but I still wouldn't give it a 5.10a.

name: Tradmania
description: Thin crack, lots of finger sized stuff.  Slightly overhung start, 2 great ledges to rest on.  Crux is right before the 2nd ledge where the crack gets really tiny and the face is less feartured.  Stick through it and reach for large jugs right over the ledge.

name: Two Minute Crack
description: Nasty large crack going along the left dihedral of Rock-A-Bye Baby chimney/arete.

name: Unknown
description: This is a new route so the rock is fairly dirty.  Large variety of holds as the rock runs semi-jagged all the wall to the chains.

name: The Bitter End
description: This route has every kind of hold from crimps, slopers, gastons, to underclings.  Lots of technical moves.  Weird finish.  5.11d?

name: Buffy the Tendon Slayer
description: Buffy is the longest and hardest climb on the Northeast wall.  There are two possible starts which make vary slightly in difficulty.  Crux is definitely near the top where you follow an overhanging rounded arete and bust a mono to get over the bulge.

name: Clip Me Deadly
description: Sketchy crimps and pinches to small hump.  Look for small jugs hidden along the top of the hump. Finish on easy stuff.  Short and Sweet

name: Dark Justice
description: A great route!  Start with hard moves to jugs.  Make tricky moves on small gaston, pockets, and sidepulls up to crux around 5th bolt, with an easier finish to chains.  ENDURANCE ANYONE?

name: Equilibrium
description: Not sure if there is a crux.  Pump over bulge then follow flake/seam all the way up.  Fun route.

name: The Good Reverend Christopher Martin
description: Very short and powerful route, though it's pretty sweet! Crux is basically from the 4th move until after sticking the hold just above the first bolt. After that, it's just fun, easier movement to the chains. May be flooded right underneath during the early summer.

name: Todd's Mole Hill
description: Older climb that needs maintenance.  Got some fun boulder moves, but very short.  Lots of hidden holds.

name: Trad
description: Not a popular route as it is relatively short and the start is very tricky and technical (bring a stick clip if that's a problem).  Crimpy moves follow tiny seem up to massive pockets.

name: Unknown
description: Route starts at Dark Justice than moves from jugs to the right toward Wicked Game.  Continue traversing right and finish on Equilibrium.

name: Wicked Game
description: Work up small hump to massive jug.  Make killer moves through sparse pockets up to diagonal rail.  Crux in my opinion is at pockets, which makes it a bad spot as you could hit the ground if you peel off when you're clipping and have too much slack out (maybe it's just psychological). Just don't miss the pockets.  Pretty much over when you hit the rail.  Route curves right at the top with an easier finish.

name: Hanging Humor
description: This route is the highest at Heise Rock, and provides the most exposure.  Easy scramble up to first bolt.  Second bolt is closer than it looks, just go for it and watch those feet (a little slick).  Work under two small roofs before tackling the big one.  Huge underclings with big throw for massive jugs and pockets.  The topout is a piece of cake since you've got big holds, but if you're pumped it could be difficult.

name: Pigeon crack
description: Big gear down low and hand size gear up top.  A very large family of doves lives in this crack and tend to deficate on it a lot.

name: Retro Man
description: Climb the face over small bulge; then right to anchors. Pumpy

name: Seeking Sleazy Squeezes
description: Start right of Rock Ninja at jugs, using crack to pull yourself over the bulge.  Face climb through pumpy moves and over lip to anchors. A must do!

name: Wango Tango
description: Bouldery start through great jugs.  Continue up through increasingly sketchier moves.  Merge with Seeking Sleazy Squeezes to share same finish.

name: All American Man
description: 10 bolts.  good sustained face climb with crux 3/4 way up. Another of Massacre's best.  "nerd crack" to the right is off route.

name: Banana Splits
description: 11D direct start (2 bolts), or easier and much more popular variation starting just right up a corner until possible to move left into the classic stemming dihedral, 11A

name: Fireworks on the Fourth
description: Sustained, steep, good rock.  Difficult crux comes at 3/4 height after a small roof on thin finger locks.

name: Fried Chicken
description: bolts up dihedral right of Banana Splits

name: Gear Jammer
description: Retrobolted pro crack.  AKA Lock and Load

name: If I Had An English Accent
description: First bolted route on the far left side of All American Wall

name: Kitty Hawk
description: Good climb. Bolts and a dubious looking pin that isn't crucial for protecting this route.

name: Little Big Man
description: 7 bolts. Blocky

name: Main Street
description: Super popular warmup for the area.  Shares last bolt and top anchors with Wall Street.

name: Miss American Pie
description: Shares first 5 bolts with Fireworks on the Fourth, then traverse right at small roof finish up steep, cruxy bulge on 3 more bolts.

name: Peanut Gallery
description: 4 bolts.  Just right of Snickers

name: Pretty Woman
description: 10 bolts.  Starts just right of a brown bulge.  Sustained 11a climbing.  One of Massacre's best.

name: Rock-A-Billy
description: 7 bolts up difficult thin slab to a big move over at a bulge.  Shares 1st bolt, the pin, and the top anchors with Kitty Hawk.

name: Snickers
description: about 15 yards right of Fireworks on the Fourth.  Scramble up past one bolt to a big platform to belay, then 4 more bolts.

name: Sticky Situation
description: 11d. Six bolts up crack/face.  Save some for the crux at top.

name: Ugly Old Man
description: Variation to Pretty Woman, clip first 3 bolts of PW then move left for 6 more bolts to an independent sport anchor.

name: Wall Street
description: Fun bolted climb right of Fried Chicken.  Shares last bolt and top anchors with Main Street.

name: Barbie
description: Right of and shares anchors with GI Joe.  Good exposure.

name: Biscuits and Gravy
description: Crack/inside corner.  Fun but the bolts are a little spaced out.

name: Burnt Toast
description: 4 bolts up blunt prow, thin crimping on excellent rock. Right of Sunny Side Up.

name: Butt Cleavage
description: Face just left of arete with hollow sounding flakes.  Really fun,... but will the flakes stay?  Pumpy.  Shares anchors with Totally Agricultural.

name: Coyote Bait
description: Excellent thin slab moves to a burly pull onto the steep upper face.

name: Cracker Jacker
description: Sustained left facing corner to a stance at about 3/4 height. Short, thin finish lead to the top anchors.

name: Famous Potatoes
description: Awesome pockets.

name: Fire Flies
description: Pro crack in prominent left facing dihedral with fixed pin at top.

name: Fire Inside
description: Left leaning arete.

name: G.I. Joe
description: Right of Lolita.  Bulge at top. Shares top anchors with Barbie.

name: Lolita
description: Right of and shares last bolt and top anchors with Whining Babies.

name: Migrant Labor
description: Starts right of and shares finish with Rodeo Queen. Awkward moves up the prow.

name: Moonbeam
description: Just right of Sunshine and is the furthest right route on the Rural Wall.

name: Prize Fight
description: Climb a pillar formation to a fun, steep headwall finish.

name: Rawhide
description: Starts in a corner/slot right of Coyote Bait left of Whining Babies.  Fun jugs.  Better than Whining Babies.

name: Rodeo Queen
description: Short cruxy start to a cruiser finish on decent rock.  Shares finish and top anchors with Migrant Labor.

name: Rosy the Riveter
description: Start a little left and pull through a bulge to a stance below a roof, work up and right to a classic face shield.

name: Sunny Side Up
description: This is a rare climb in that it is one of the few bolted climbs at Massacre Rocks easier than 5.9.    Scramble up and belay on the ledge.  Follow the bolts on nice rock.

name: Sunshine
description: Right of Cracker Jacker.

name: Tick Fever
description: Work up a shallow corner to a difficult mono crux to finish on huge 5.9 pockets. Fun.

name: Totally Agricultural
description: Face climb up to the right side of a blunt arete.  Fun move pulling left around the prow up high. Starts right of and shares anchors with Butt Cleavage.

name: Whining Babies
description: Hard slabby move at the bottom and an awkward finish with fun, pleasant climbing on good rock in between.

name: Working Man
description: Follow a right facing dihedral corner crack into the box dihedral which has multiple possibilites to gain the anchors.

name: Acapulco Cliff Diving
description: As the South of Border wall continues right around a corner, the route on the corner is Acapulco Cliff Diving.  Scramble up a grassy ledge to pull on the rock at the first bolt.  Fun facing climbing leads to a pull onto the arete for an airy finish.

name: The Breeze
description: Follow bolts up wide corner.

name: Caca-Mongo
description: Big line on a steep face.

name: Cartoon Violence
description: Start on a blunt arete and climb to a thin crux finish on a steep headwall.

name: Cinco de Mayo
description: Fun opening moves lead to a dirtier finish.  Newer route might clean up with a few ascents.

name: Dos Equis
description: Boulder up to big ledge and follow right line of bolts up shallow corner to a suspicious wedged flake at mid height.  This flake has been load tested by hundreds of climbers but assume nothing and proceed cautiously to fun cruiser upper face.

name: Easier Said Than Done
description: Follow bolts in the dihedral to a tricky move left to the top anchors of Star Spangled Banger.

name: El Grande Corvette
description: Shallow corner, stem and jam sustained moves on good rock to the top anchors.

name: Fiesta
description: Bolts and sport climbing up a wide left facing corner. Fun.

name: Hasta La Hoopla
description: Thin bouldery moves at the start lead to thuggy moves around a bulge.

name: The Hobo
description: Fun, steep white face.

name: I-Chi-Hua-Hua
description: Starts out left side of low roof and pulls into the sustain classic corner on suburb rock.

name: Jalapeno
description: Finishes up wide crack.

name: Jose Can You See
description: Steep tricky, pumpy face climbing on excellent brown rock.

name: Little Miss Muffet
description: On the east face of South of Border and about 20 feet from Acapulco Cliff Diving, start on a ramp and work up a brown face to a corner.

name: Low Rider
description: Start near white corner and pull on to brown face climbing to the top anchors.

name: Mexican Standoff
description: Hard face climbing past first few bolts on great brown rock leads to an easier finish.

name: Pasta La Poopla
description: Start at grey and white striped rock staying right of a small ledge. Look for a hidden pocket to make it come it at grade.  May be harder.

name: Roadrunner Roof
description: Start in a creamy white dihedral and exits out the left side of a big roof.  Shares Anchors with Cartoon Violence.

name: Run For the Border
description: Technical face climbing up shallow slightly overhanging dihedral. Sustained movement.

name: Speedy Gonzales
description: Boulder up to big ledge and follow left line of bolts up corner to very fun face and steep finish to the anchors.

name: Star Spangled Banger
description: Excellent jug haul on blunt arete.  Super fun.

name: Stella
description: Blocky start leads to ramp to the final shallow and slightly overhanging chimney.

name: Teguilla Sunrise
description: Overhanging white face around the corner from Caca-Mongo.  There is an unknown, possibly unfinished hard looking mixed line with a fixed cam and one bolt just to left.  This could be Massacre's hardest route.

name: The Tick
description: Start up the white face, then pulls directly over the big roof on powerful, crimpy moves.  Boulder problem crux maybe goes at V7.

name: Tres Hombres
description: Short, intense route up brown, blunt arete.

name: Zorro
description: Fun start up corner system to a face and pull into a slightly spicy finish.

name: And
description: Stiff 3 bolt variation straight up the prow between Thelma and Louise. Joins Thelma for the last 3 bolts.

name: Border Town
description: Great looking face climb on brown rock.

name: Caboose
description: Stem up left side of a big block, crux finish.

name: Derailed
description: Face to arete, using the crack to the left avoids the crux.

name: Dream On
description: Excellent route. Start on the ledge behind the juniper tree and climb on great pockets to a wild, steep scoop.

name: Kitty's Corner
description: Big right facing corner.

name: Loco-Motive
description: First route on the left side of the T&L Area.  Nice face.

name: Louise
description: Work up the right side of the prow and cross over for the last bolt and top anchors of Thelma.

name: The Terminator
description: Climb the white face and over the prominent roof. Going up the right side of the wall to the roof is easier (~11D).

name: Thelma
description: A prominent buttress in the T&L area has the routes Thelma, And, Louise.  All share the same top anchor.  Thelma is the on the left aspect of the buttress.  Holds stay left of the first couple bolts making it feel a little contrived.  Once you commit to the face, it's a fun climb to the top.

name: Women on the Loose
description: Fun face climbing after a blocky start up a shallow arete feature.

name: Anchors Away
description: Work up a thin slab to gain a slightly overhanging flared corner.  Find a couple key technical jams and follow the corner to the top.

name: Cat on a Leash
description: Start in a thin crack in a right facing corner.  Move up and right to a thin arete finish.

name: Comeback Kid
description: Climb up the right hand crack in a deep double dihedral. Transition to the left hand crack and continue to the top.

name: Doggie Doo
description: Steep route that diagonals right on good holds to a thin crux finish.

name: Dukes of Hazard
description: Thin tips crack starts in a shallow corner.

name: Hands Up
description: Obvious right diagonal hand crack to a sport anchor.

name: Happiness is a Warm Gun
description: Climb through a low bulge.  Continues to a thin face. Long reaches and sustained.

name: The Horror
description: Corner system, watch the clip at the 3rd bolt - scary.

name: Little Miss Can't Be Wrong
description: Climb up into a corner system to the top.

name: Lonesome Dove
description: Climb up past a white/tan streak and finish on a steep brown face.

name: Path Illogical
description: Boulder up a the arete of a prow past two bolts and finish on the last two bolts of Resistance is Futile.

name: Resistance is Futile
description: Out the right side of a low roof to a face above with a couple bolts.

name: Termite Velocity
description: Climb a left leaning flared crack to a small bulge.  Step left onto a pretty brown face.  Using somewhat hidden mailbox slot pockets, face climb up to a stance just below the top anchors.

name: Your Hine Ass
description: Thin boulder problem start, eases some at mid height.

name: Air Of The Dog
description: Climb past a huge flake and continue up the sustained climb.  Good fun.

name: Barely There
description: Up a flare to a dihedral, upper climbing just right of Ruffled Feathers

name: Big Balls in Cow Town
description: Classic line up left trending dihedral.

name: Big Hair
description: Up face to crux roofs near the top.

name: Birdcage
description: Up left crack for 3 bolts, then traverse hard right to a left facing dihedral and continue to the top anchors.

name: Bullets and Butterfly Wings
description: Finger crack through a roof to steep slabs above.  Excellent.

name: Cornholio
description: Up corners to a steep face.  Would be a good route but the clips are purposely designed to give a *particular* short person a hard time.  Not cool.  Rumor is that the FA person is coming back to fix the clips.

name: Cow Town Stud
description: Excellent variation climb. Clip first 5 bolts of Big Balls in Cow Town, then right up steep face to anchors.

name: D.O.A. (aka Dan's Out of Action)
description: Sick flared start to a pumpy middle section to a wild finish.  Named in honor of a "busted finger" first ascent.

name: The Diving Board
description: Start on The Perch then goes straight up the right side of the jutting flake.

name: Eagle Feather
description: Variation route between Rap-Tour and Ruffled Feathers.  Best to belay on big half way ledge.  May need some gear for the belay.

name: The Eagle Has Landed
description: Classic stemming with thin tips and micro edges.  Short, fun route.  Ends part way up the wall.

name: Easy Does It
description: Start on a blocky section to gain a big left facing corner, pull through the bulge and trend slightly left to the top anchors.  Probably Eagle Wall's easiest route but no give away.

name: Fire Away
description: Start up Tour de Pump, then left up the blunt arete. May be Massacre's best 12a/b.

name: Flies On A Hotdog
description: Excellent moderate route on a hard wall.  Starts in big dihedral and trends up and slightly right staying in the corner until a steep exposed finish.

name: Free As A Bird
description: Corner to wide crack to face.

name: Free Bird
description: Work up to a tricky traverse right to the arete, then on to a good, steep finish.

name: Helter Skelter
description: Follow bolts out of the cave, then up and right to mid-way anchors.

name: Layla
description: Line just left of a small arete.

name: My Main Squeeze
description: Up and right into a dihedral.

name: One Bad Stud
description: Same start as She Ain't Pretty ..., then diagonal left up steep face; sustained and excellent.

name: The Perch
description: Funky start leads to fun moves around the left side and up on a big jutting flake (the perch), then liebacks up a shallow dihedral.

name: Rap-Tour
description: One of the best moderate routes at Massacre.  Tricky start up a boulder to a deep overhanging corner then to a long, feature climb up the left side of very nice looking brown face.

name: Ruffled Feathers
description: Funky moves through gritty huecos lower down lead to excellent, sustained face climbing up the right side of the a big brown face.  Cruxy at the finish.

name: Scary Little Crack
description: Same start as Birdcage then straight up crack/dihedral through some potentially loose blocks.

name: She Ain't Pretty, She Just Looks That Way
description: Up shallow sustained corner on tip jams and stems. Move slightly left to a overhanging, pumpy finish.

name: She's A Screamer
description: Starts on the left side of the "big cave" at the base, pull over the roof, continue left to great arete climbing.

name: Sideswiped
description: 2 bolt variation of Sidewinder.

name: Sidewinder
description: Traverse right into a flared feature, continue up the face to the arete.

name: Smooth Talker
description: Move right up a slab start into a slot, then finish on a steep face.

name: Stumped
description: Left most bolt line on the lower left side of Eagle Wall.  Short, hard.

name: Tour de Pump
description: Up left leaning ramp then work right across a face to a slot.  Steep, pumpy finish.

name: Wildfire
description: Face climb up to an arete for a ways, then move left onto steep, sustained face.  Fantastic climb.

name: [Redacted]
description: Short overhaning corner - hard!!

name: Barney Rubble
description: Bolt line up flace to wide slot to face finish.

name: Bird of Prey
description: Same start as Prairie Dog, then right to nice, sustained arete/face.

name: Bladerunner
description: Climb a huge wild looking flake.

name: Blood, Sweat, and Beers
description: Brutally hard climb.  Wild 12a roof lead to harder crux moves at the last two bolts.

name: Daydream Believer
description: Move up hard layback, continue up flared corner, then good face climbing to Bird of Prey finish.

name: The Disease
description: Right of Bird of Prey.  Blocky finish with possible loose rock.

name: Father Time
description: Warm up for the area.  Tricky moves off a couple blocky stances.

name: Good and Plenty
description: Excellent variation.  Climb past the second bulge on Happy Happy Joy Joy and at the top of the big dihedral work out right to another corner system. Continue straight up to the top anchors.  Manage rope drag.

name: Happy  Happy Joy Joy
description: Pull a bulge at the start, work up to another bulge with a hard pull into a big dihedral.  Work up the dihedral until it is possible to hand traverse out left before continuing on fun rock to the top anchors.

name: Overseer
description: Negotiate a tricky bulge then layback through a crux roof.

name: Prairie Dog
description: Tricky moves through a bulge, then up big dihedral with a big loose-looking block.

name: Zippity-Do-Da
description: Thin crack/seam crux.

name: Echo Phobia
description: Climb the prow to a stance then follow the face to the top anchors.

name: Flambe
description: Bolt line up center of overhanging face passing two roof/overlaps on the way to the final headwall.  Massacre's most sustained route?!?

name: Flame On
description: Slightly easier 5 bolt variation to Flambe. Work up a face and pass the first overlap near it's right side.  Continue up a crack into a corner and pass the second overlap also on the right.  Then move left on a thin, steep face to join Flambe for the last 3 bolts and top anchors.

name: King Kong
description: Hard face and corners.

name: Out Of The Flying Pan
description: Follow 5 bolts up a grey corner and pull left to a stance and join Echo Phobia for 3 more bolts to the top anchors.

name: Yo-Yo-Ma-Ma
description: Work up a crack, hueco's and a flake to pass a bulge into a to deep slot.  Follow the corner up, work right and finish on a headwall block.

name: Daffy
description: Climb the thin crack on the end of the block, gain a stance low then pull through an awkward slot to fun but tricky face climbing above.

name: Goofy
description: Short, fierce problem. On the right side of the block start with a hard pull off the ground then up a sustained blunt arete.

name: Legends of the Fall
description: Left hand route on a short, very steep wall.

name: Mickey
description: Up the left side of the big block then angle right.

name: Minnie
description: The crux is right at the start. It was tough! JB said more like a 10b. Once you got off the ground and over the first ledge it was quite a bit easier.

name: Samurai Warrior
description: Right hand route of two short, very steep climbs.

name: Die Laughing
description: Seemed a lot easier than Minnie (10a/b). Flashed it on top rope (JB leading)

name: Funny Business
description: Start to the right of Good For A Laugh Or Two and climb directly to the short dihedral.  Pull up onto the big ledge.  Hard laybacking off the ledge leads to more face climbing.  Don't blow the second clip off the ledge.

name: Giggles
description: Great dihedral and fun climbing.  Clip the first 3 bolts of Yuk It Up and move into the right facing dihedral.  Lieback, jam, and stem to the top anchors.

name: Good For A Laugh Or Two
description: Pull a bulge and diagonal up and right to a short dihedral.  At the top of the dihedral do a hard pull on to a steep face and follow the face/seam to the top.

name: Hee Haw
description: Right most bolt line of the Funny Business Area.

name: The Improv
description: Work up the arete between two corner systems.

name: Joke'em if They Can't Take a Fuck
description: Pull onto the slab and work up a cream colored streak with a thin seam.  Continue into a shallow left facing corner.

name: Jokes On You
description: Climb up a shallow left facing corner to a stance on the right.  Continue up a right facing corner until you can move out right to the top anchors.  Crux in each corner

name: Just For Laughs
description: Right around the end of Funny Business Wall the crag has two more climbs.  After a blocky start the route gets steep and has excellent, sustained face climbing to the top anchors.

name: Kamikaze
description: Short, manufactured route from the early 90's.  Hard pulls on drilled mono-digit pockets.

name: Kermit The Frog
description: Work up a tough flared left facing dihedral to a stance on the right.  Step left back into the corner and pull the short bulge with gymnastics moves and a jam or two.  Continue to the top anchors.

name: No Laughing Matter
description: Start under a close to the ground roof and pull onto a slab.  Continue up corners/cracks to the top anchors.

name: The Punchline
description: Steep face climbing right of the Giggles corner.  Clip the first bolt of Yuk/Giggles then move slightly right up independent bolt line.  Sustained, steep finish.

name: Sick Humor
description: Climb onto the slab and continue up as it steepens.  Second crux on the more featured rock above.

name: Slab Stick
description: At the first bolt pull up right onto the slab and work the steepening face with a hand on the arete and a hand in the shallow corner/seam.  Fun climbing.

name: Stand-Up Comedy
description: Climb up the prow of the Funny Business Wall, several technical cruxes.

name: Vegematic
description: Carefully climb over a grassy spot with a small bush at the bolt to good climbing in the left facing corner above.

name: What a Crack Up
description: Looooved this climb! Crux right at the top where you have to climb a crack to get to the top. JB led, I followed on top rope. My first taste of crack - and I became instantly addicted!

name: Yuk It Up
description: Work up a few bolts to the base of blunt arete/buttress.  Very hard moves through the bulge lead to slightly easier but sustained climbing to the top.

name: All 'Lit Up
description: Start in corner with dark rock and pass a horizontal feature at mid height.  Continue trending slightly left to the top anchors.

name: Crack o' Lighting
description: This is a crunch start on the prominent white'ish blocks a couple feet left of the vertical crack. Start crunched, traverse right through the under cling, horizontal, crack until you arrive at the vertical crack. Use vertical crack for hands while edges and smears for the feet. Top out on easy, but potentially loose, rock.

name: I Saw the Light
description: Climb white and grey streaked, featured rock up to a short headwall and pull into a very shallow brown corner below the top anchors.

name: Light in the Loafers
description: Climb up coarse bubbly rock until you can pull on to a grey face.  Continue up into a prominent corner that leads to the top anchors.

name: Light My Fire
description: Follow a left trending seam in grey rock to a horizontal crack at mid-height.  Continue straight up to the top anchors.

name: Lighten Up
description: Follow a shallow corner to the right side of a shallow arete.

name: Lightning
description: Climb grey and white face below a a prominent roof.  Pass the roof on the left side.

name: Lights Out
description: Furthest left route, starts in white streaked dihedral.

name: Thunder
description: Follow "Lightning up to the prominent roof and follow big holds out to the apex of the roof.  Pass the apex on the left side on thin crimps to a big pull to a decent edge.  Continue on easier ground to the top.

name: Trippin' the Light Fantastic
description: Face climb the right side of big white patch to the right side of the prominent roof.  Pass the roof on it's right side pulling slightly left into a shallow brown corner below the top anchors.

name: The Gong Show
description: 8 bolts, stemming crux low leads to harder, sustained face climbing above

name: Password
description: 6 Bolts, tough slot start, kinky stand-up, face finish

name: The Price is Right
description: Climbs wavy features to a stance and jugs under and to the right of a roof. Scoot across the shield and end in a right-facing dihedral.

name: T. S. Productions
description: 6 bolts, blocky start, through slot, then stem roof, finishes on the face ( don't wimp out right!)

name: What's Behind Door #3?
description: 5 bolts, stem start to pumpy block/crack climbing above

name: What's My Line
description: 5 bolts, scramble up ledge to first bolt

name: [Redacted]
description: Best moderate route on the Gang Fight Wall and super fun.  Pull up through some great hueco's and buckets to a roof. Pull through and climb to the top anchors.

name: Caught In The Line Of Fire
description: Climb up to a small bulge and pass it on the right, at the top trend left to the Graffiti top anchors.

name: Cement Shoes
description: Short hard route.

name: The Chump
description: Awkward bulge crux.

name: Cocky Young Men
description: Hard moves of a bulge.

name: Crack
description: Steep flakes to a small roof and a box dihedral.

name: Do The Right Thing
description: Excellent climb up a thin crack in shallow corner.

name: Gang Fight
description: Follow a line through a grey streak just to the right of the obvious black streak.

name: Graffiti
description: Line up to a thin crack/face.

name: Grumpy Old Men (aka John and Dan)
description: Technical brown face.

name: Hit Man
description: Through the left side of the obvious roof, then follow a left trending line.

name: The Knife Fight
description: Several struggles up a nice looking brown prow.

name: Mean Streak
description: Extremely thin moves up the obvious black streak.

name: The Rumble
description: Finger pockets through the center of the obvious roof, fun and athletic moves.

name: The Switchblade
description: Fantastic, sustained climb.

name: Trigger Happy
description: Right trending line with a few sharp jams on the way to the top anchors.

name: West Side Story
description: Short line on the left side of Gang Fight Wall

name: Zip Gun
description: Up the right side of the roof and follow a prow.

name: Black Velvet Elvis
description: Committing stemming to a top out on a column.

name: Burning Love
description: Climb up and left to a face and sidepull crux before rejoining Black Velvet Elvis for the finish.

name: Don't be Cruel
description: Technical dihedral, sustained and good movement.

name: Now or Never
description: Start with a short boulder section protected by a bolt to a ledge. This sustained line is an excellent combination of powerful moves and technical pockets. The anchor is typical of Massacre and could use replacing, due to the sharpness of one of the fixed carabiners.

name: All Naturale
description: Formerly a trad line, now retro-bolted. Follow crack up to roof.  Both right and left variations are bolted.  Left crack is slightly harder.

name: French Kissing
description: Retro-bolted pro crack.

name: French Toast
description: Same start as The Guillotine, then up corner to crack to slot.

name: The Guillotine
description: Stemming start over small roofs lead to a crux bulge.

name: Honor Amongst Fiends
description: Start on the right side of a little roof just off the ground and continue up a sustained face.

name: Mon Amie
description: Climb an arete to gain a face.

name: Mr. McGoo
description: Climb the rampy left facing dihedral and work up to a hard finish with a hidden hold.

name: Pepe La'Peau
description: Stay just right of the roofs and follow a fun face to the top anchors.

name: Solitaire
description: Just left of a manky wide crack.

name: This Schmoo's For You
description: Excellent climb, standard for the grade at Massacre.  Steep hueco's past the "Schmoo" lead to  one rest before a bulge and an extremely thin finish.

name: Totally French
description: Steep face left of big roof.  Exciting headwall shield finish.  Excellent, scintillating moves!

name: Truffles
description: Weird but good rock to a steep headwall finsih.

name: Water Lilly
description: Bolt line about 50 feet right of French Toast

name: Water Louie
description: Psycho liebacking!

name: Whee-Whee
description: Hard start out of a small roof, and hard finish if  you go up from the 4th bolt.  According to the route builder, off route if you hand traverse right after the the 3rd bolt.

name: Half Pint
description: The route has a plethora of features for hands and feet. Finding the correct holds is probably the crux around the second bolt.

name: Pee Wee
description: This Climb has a big move right off the ground to great holds.

name: Small Fry
description: Stemming is the name of the game on this route.

name: [Redacted]
description: A short route more of a boulder problem, however a rope is nice. A relentless route with little room to rest. Start on a good side pull,to a sloper, with a sweet drop knee to obtain your way up the crack.

name: Aphrodisiac
description: Relentless, thin, creative footwork.

name: Aphrodite
description: Link-up. Starts on French Connection to Aphrodisiac finish.

name: French Connection
description: Awkward start to a amazing overhanging acrobatic jug haul.

name: Kama-Sutra
description: Another link up. 7 bolts traverse from French Connection to Love on the Rocks.

name: La Femme Nikita
description: Pockets, pumpy.

name: Love Connection
description: Another steep pump fest on shallow pockets and thin edges.

name: Love on the Rocks
description: Another steep, short pumpy route.

name: One Night Fling
description: Clip the first bolt of Love On The Rocks and move right for 3 more bolts to the top anchors.

name: Orgasmatron
description: New addition as of Fall 2019, furthest route on the left. Follow cool runnel things with cool lay back side pulls back stepping both directions.

name: Dim Reefer
description: Not a lot know about this one.

name: Grim R.P. er
description: Fixed pin, starts on cute little arch

name: Hole-In-The-Wall
description: Chimney in deep corner

name: Moonstruck
description: Bolts over spooky, blocky roof, fun upper face.

name: Sundance
description: Bolted arete

name: Three Dogs for a Dollar
description: Bolted Slab/face

name: Birddog
description: Starts on first three bolts of The Mongrel, then straight up, over kinky bulge to steep, fun face.

name: Chili Dog
description: Crack System

name: Deputy Dog
description: Natural pro crack

name: Dog At Large
description: Another good bolt line

name: The Dog Catcher
description: Starts in wide crack, up bulge, steep upper face/corner.

name: Dog Fight
description: Natural Pro Crack

name: The Dog Pound
description: Bolt line through ship's prowl arete

name: Dog Slide
description: Link-up; Start on Dog At Large, finish on Slip Slide'n Away

name: Lethal Rejection
description: Bolted bulge to steep headwall.

name: The Mad Dog
description: Wild pro your own crack

name: The Mongrel
description: Good bolt line, several cruxes.

name: Obedience School
description: Another pro your own crack

name: Outlaw Trail
description: Large Crack

name: Air Thee Well
description: Pro your own line, crack to slab, to overhanging headwall, classic

name: Be Scared And Hold On Tight
description: Wild slab, through roof, to overhanging crack

name: Country Rhodes
description: Crack through bulge, direct finish would be good, harder, needs bolts

name: Cruisen'n The Strip
description: Cracks left and right are off route, or its easier,

name: Freeway
description: One-bolt start, wanders, finish in steep open book with log at top

name: Grease Monkey
description: Bolted slab

name: Off-Ramp
description: Cruxy at second-to- third bolt, finish on steep arete

name: Overpass
description: Good moderate natural pro line up book/crack, through roof (crux)

name: Sherlock Moans
description: Broken and loose up to a large ledge (60 feet), then a cool pocketed arete.     Bruce Black gave this route 2 stars; I found it to be pretty unpleasant.

name: Slip Slid'n Away
description: Bolts up steep slab (crux), then fun, but somewhat run-out climbing up arete. Left of large, right-facing corner system, sport anchors

name: Streets of Fire
description: Bolts, arete finish

name: Ted's Date Route
description: Pro-your-own line through bulge, up nice slot/book

name: The Bully at Muscle Beach
description: 120 FEET Test piece, bolts, first crux (Muscle Beach) is 12A; overhanging headwall finish (The Bully) has crux at top

name: Career of the 90's
description: 120 FEET 12 bolts, great moves

name: Castles Made of Sand
description: Follow Dirty Dancing for 3 bolts, then head left into the dihedral.

name: Crank Calls
description: 120 FEET Bolt line through kinky slot, then left to steep headwall

name: Debra Winger
description: 'Classic face and laybacks

name: Dirty Dancing
description: 11 bolts, up and a bit right through overhanging plates and cracks

name: Disturbing the Peace
description: Bolted, always steep

name: Get a Grip
description: Great! Continuously cruxy

name: Get Primate or Fly Mate
description: Bolts up thin, flared crack, then face finish

name: Good Flyday
description: Overhanging bolted face, several cruxes, good for a pump!

name: Gravitron
description: Kind of grubby

name: Ho! Yo-Yo-Yo!
description: Starts on poor rock, finish moves are worth the climb

name: Honey Come Down
description: 115 FEET Goes through roof/bulge, up headwall, continuously cruxy

name: Jack the Whipper
description: Classic overhanging face to finger crack, 10 bolts

name: Joy Ride
description: 120 FEET Bolts, shares several moves with Crank Calls, then goes right, up through wide slot

name: Lock-Up
description: 110 FEET: Lots of climbing, wild finish

name: Mass-A- Crack
description: 120 FEET Great pro-your-own crack through flared roof, to bolts on overhanging headwall

name: Meltdown
description: 120 FEET Pro crack to headwall, then left and up with bolts

name: Missing Link
description: 115 FEET The original line on the wall and one of the best, 15 bolts

name: Mommy's Little Monster
description: 110 FEET 13 bolts, rap chain half way, upper part is easier and real fun

name: The Mummy
description: Pro crack through roof

name: Nasty Dread Locks
description: Long and hard, with several variations, right finish is the best and hardesr

name: Snow Job
description: 125 FEET Bolts up face and flared crack, shares a move or two with Toxic Socks, pumpy, steep, crack/face finish

name: Time Keeps on Slip'n, Slip'n, Slip'n
description: Pro crack, crux at upper arching finger crack, sustained, 60' to sport anchors

name: Totally Tubular
description: Pro crack, finishes on bolted headwall

name: Toxic Socks Syndrome
description: 125 FEET Bolts, pumpy!

name: Voodoo Child
description: Short, Steep, Fun

name: Waylaid
description: 120 FEET Crux at flare/roof

name: Waylaid Pillar
description: 2 bolts, hard clips

name: White Thrash
description: Short, always hard, leaver-biner at roof

name: Wingin' in the Rain
description: Crack through roof, face finish, steep and hard

name: Yolanda
description: Bolt line up hard face, wild bulge, good steep headwall finish, 125' or rap half way (wimpy!)

name: All Jammed Up
description: 130+ FEET Pro crack, first part is somewhat dirty, past pin, to right-facing corner; upper face is fantastic, pumpy climbing

name: Black Tide
description: 120+ FEET About 15 bolts, long and steep

name: Danger Zone
description: Kind of sandy, but great movement on large knobs and slopers, leading to a technical slab finish.    .12a line goes diagonally left, avoiding the rest ledge.

name: Firefall
description: 130 FEET Through bulge/roof, sustained, continuously technical, good in spite of some flaky rock

name: A Surprise For Mom
description: (A Mother's Day gift!) Bolted face/arete, steep, great power moves of small holds

name: Airwaves
description: Bolted line

name: AM/FM
description: Bolted line, unknown

name: Ambushed
description: Crux at bush, (good hand hold!?) lots of  good climbing. NOTE: climbs over a Canadian goose nest; don"t climb this route in the spring if geese are around.

name: Chasing Wild Geese
description: Pro crack, shares overhanging crack with Cooked Goose, then left up crack system

name: Chorus Line
description: 120 FEET Same start as Swing Dancing, but go right after chimney; great "date" climb, good natural pro, varied

name: Cooked Goose
description: Bolted face to bolted overhanging crack, to arete finish, plenty of great, hard climbing

name: Delux Aggrevation
description: 130 FEET Pro crack , starts in corner, through roof and bulges, past fixed pin, finish on steep headwall.

name: In Your Face
description: Filthy start, good crux move over bulge, good 5.11 climbing above

name: The Pillar
description: Natural crack line, using only the top bolt for finish face moves

name: Public Enema #1
description: Enjoyable, crux is from second-to-third bolt, steep, pumpy finish

name: Robbin' The Cradle
description: Thin crack, short-but groovy

name: The Slot Machine
description: 125 FEET Hard and sustained from the start, the crux is above the midway anchors, arete finish, excellent!

name: The Slots
description: Natural crack above the mid-way anchors on The Slot Machine, straight up or left into the corner

name: Stand By For Technical Difficulties
description: Bolts, unknown

name: The Stranger
description: Strange moves! Step left at crux, then up and right

name: Swing Dancing
description: 120 FEET Corner to chimney, then left to face with thin crack

name: The Weenie
description: Controversial bolt addition to The Pillar; stemming left and clipping bolts makes it easier and wimpy

name: A Face In The Crowd
description: Enjoyable bolted face

name: Ah Vue Raggae
description: 125 FEET Bolt line up face, through roof/bulge, onto slab face

name: The Austin Shuffle
description: 125 FEET Natural crack/corner system through left corner/roofs, good. RIP Austin

name: The Beta Garden
description: Starts on first two bolts of Dorque Converter, then up and left, finishes on great arete

name: Bop 'Til You Drop
description: 125 FEET Through bulges, wild layback crux, hard clip!

name: Born To Be Wild
description: Bolts up white face

name: Calling Elvis
description: Short blunt arete

name: Critical Mass
description: Great bolt line, crux is above the ledge, then sustained face, technical and pumpy

name: Dancing With Myself
description: 100+ FEET Roof start to slab/face to steep finish

name: Dorque Converter
description: 110 FEET Bolt line, shares  start with Beta Garden, then right and up overhanging headwall; technical, pumpy, great!

name: If You Ain't Cranking It, You Must Be Spanki'n It
description: Bolts, starts on upper ledge, 60'

name: If You're Not Pro'n It, You're Blown It
description: Natural crack line/corner system inside right facing corner, through roof

name: Life Of Riley
description: 125 FEET Crux is bulge half-way up

name: Marty's Wild Idea
description: 12??? Project

name: Recreational Vehicles
description: 9 bolts about 25 yards right of Salty Buggers

name: Salty Buggers
description: 9 Bolts, several cruxes

name: Twist & Shout
description: Pro crack to anchors

name: Vanna White
description: Top rope project on ledge above broken rock

name: Above The Law
description: Roof/slot crux start to fun upper climbing

name: Doggy Style Arete
description: Wild atete, pumpy headwall

name: Hosstyle
description: Bolts up left-facing corner; good luck with this one!!

name: Something Wild
description: Bolted slab/face, colored hangers

name: Wild At Heart
description: Bulge to face to headwall, great pump/jug hall

name: Wily E. Coyote
description: Natural crack line, right facing corner/crack, past huge loose looking block

name: Acrophobia
description: Work up a crack into a slot.

name: ADHD
description: Clip first bolt of Sociopath then step left and climb to a good finish on excellent rock.

name: Amnesia
description: Bolts up to crux flare.

name: Brain Dead But Good In Bed
description: Bolt line up overhanging flared slot. Physical, awkward moves.

name: Cat-A-Tonic
description: Thin face.

name: Chalk Therapy
description: On the right side of buttress like feature. Fun climb that starts on balancy moves that lead to steeper rock and a cool finish.

name: Coma Toes
description: Nice looking climb. Climb the between a corner and an arete to the right.  10d if you stay on the arete.

name: Committed
description: Fierce direct start to Straight Jacket.

name: Freudian Slip
description: A overhanging masterpiece.  Concave face/crack with a crux at the final headwall before the top anchors.

name: It's Time For Your Medication
description: Somewhat contrived to stay on the line of bolts.

name: Maniac
description: Bolts up white face. May be Massacre's best hard climb.

name: Oedipus Complex
description: Work through the big roof.

name: Off Your Rocker
description: Several crux sections.

name: Pathological Flyer
description: Excellent and vaired move, crux at the top.

name: Pavlov's Dogs
description: Excellent climbing on a white face just left of obvious roof.

name: Pervert's Pleasures
description: Sustained climb up two parallel seams to a dihedral finish.

name: Psycho Billy
description: Start up the left side of a huge block.

name: Psychopath
description: Excellent route with a technical face climbing crux at the bottom and the steep, pumpy crux at the top.

name: Sociopath
description: 10b if you climb on the left side of the bolt line and 10c if you force yourself to stay right of the bolt line.

name: Straight Jacket
description: Short climb up a large boulder like feature.  Climb up a black bulge/face.

name: Sweethearts Of The Rodeo
description: Bolts up the right side of the huge block then same finish as Psycho Billy.

name: Waiter, There's A Fly In My Supe
description: Work up corner to a steep finish.

name: Welcome To The Funny Farm
description: Good face moves.

name: Zigman Void
description: Shorter route compared to it's immediate neighbors. Follow bolts up 'z-seam' face.

name: Bolter's Ed
description: Another route on the blocky section of the cliff.  Steep blocky holds lead to a finish in a deep dihedral.

name: Clang
description: 2 bolts through steep terrain and move left and finish on the last two bolts of Cling.

name: Cling
description: Steep and pumpy.

name: Dry Hump
description: Short route with a hard pull at the roof.

name: Jabberwocky
description: Attractive curving brown face.  Harder than it looks.

name: The Mild Side
description: Further right another 3 bolt variation to the Wild Side. Short, fun then work left and join Wild Side.

name: Pink Slip
description: Unusual rock for Massacre, lots of blocky holds that all see to slope the wrong direction for hanging on to.  Climb to a shallow dihedral.

name: Spring Spawner
description: Short, steep, hard.

name: The Vile Side
description: 4 bolt variation to the start of the Wild Side.

name: The Wild Side
description: Starts in corner, move left onto the arete/face.  Fun headwall finish.

name: Wild Thang
description: Wild layback.

name: Back On The Chain Gang
description: Excellent route up the center of the wall.

name: Jailbreak
description: Pumpy climb up good holds and acrobatic movement, to a midway crux. Finish on a steep overhang to good holds at the top.   PROTECTION   7 bolts, sport anchors.     LOCATION   Leftmost of the three routes on Jail House Wall.

name: Stonebreaker
description: Right trending moves to a stance then left, through a bulge and a steep finish up a wide slot.    Perfect chocolate brown rock.

name: [Redacted]
description: Long, fun route.  Start on the weirdly featured rock left of Nurse Ratchet and pass a blocky section to work into a big corner with wild airy stemming before a jug haul finish on great rock.

name: Airhead
description: Bolts up hand crack to great, steep finish.

name: Daddy Needs His Medicine
description: Long retrobolted line, second half is on great rock and is really fun.

name: Dead Man Walking
description: Pull through a crack to a ledge below a double dihedral.  Continue up working both cracks.

name: Delirious
description: Next crack right of Demonic Possession.

name: Delirium Tremens
description: Right face of the pillar.

name: Demonic Possession
description: Pro crack, second crack right of Still Crazy... behind the big juniper tree.

name: Doctor Feelgood
description: 11 bolt continuation of Nurse Ratchet.

name: Everybody And Their Dog
description: Bolt line up wild, detached pillar.

name: Loco
description: Shorter route.

name: Lunatic
description: Starts on first two bolts of D.T. then moves left for 4 more bolts but finishes on the same top anchors as Delerium Tremens.

name: No Mo Natural Pro
description: Crack with bolts, might want to stick clip the first bolt.
