name: Nurse Ratchet
description: Easily identified short route up weirdly eroded chicken head like large plates.  Looks suspect but these features have been climbed hundreds of times.

name: Nut Case
description: Long retrobolted line (aka Slippin Post).  Tough, slightly dirty moves down low. Route cleans up about mid way and becomes more fun.

name: Pain Thriller
description: Starts in thin, tough finger crack, then up left for a steep face finish.

name: Seizure
description: A little contrived to stay on the arete only.  Using the crack to the right lowers the grade to 11c.

name: Serial Driller
description: Long hard route, several cruxes.

name: Sketch-O-Frantic
description: Great bolt line up the right side of the obvious blank face. Starts a little loose but gets thin and sustained through the crux bulge.

name: Special Olympics
description: Up crack to blunt, brown arete.  Thin cruxy finish.

name: Split Personality
description: Starts on a short pillar, then right.  Great climb with stemming start to a few jams to a thin face finish.

name: Still Crazy After All These Years
description: Short climb on a blunt arete with sharp edges.

name: Ted's and Marty's Wonderful Adventure
description: Long pro crack left of obvious large face up higher.

name: Wild Virus
description: Nice climb with good moves.

name: Yo Riley Crack
description: Pro crack that starts on the left side of a short pillar.

name: 5.8ish
description: Climb up through a wide, steep crack and move slightly left to finish.

name: [Redacted]
description: Work up the right side of steep outside corner until you can pull left onto a slab.  Work up over a bulge and turn another bulge around a corner to the left.

name: Black Mamba
description: Same start as Space Violator then up  and right to tricky liebacks.

name: Date Bait
description: Short sustained corner.  Too bad it's so short.

name: DV8
description: Bolt line on blunt corner up to a face.  Thin crux!

name: Face Shot
description: Short bolted face.

name: First Date
description: Pro your own corner/crack/roof.

name: Get Laid
description: Left side of large buttress formation.  Tricky lieback crux at the top.

name: Heavy Petting
description: Starts beneath a small roof and moves around left and up staying on the blunt arete.  Fun.

name: Holey Trojans
description: Left side of steep, pretty brown slab.  Thin moves!

name: Hot Date
description: Short route on in the middle the steep, slabby brown face.  Right of Holey Trojans and left of Date Bait.

name: Jeff-Boy-R.D.
description: Right facing corner to upper face.

name: The Slob
description: Another short, fun steep route.

name: Space Shot
description: Tricky bolted blunt arete/face.

name: Space Violator
description: Excellent route up center of the face with bouldery moves down low, positive edges/pockets in the middle and a steep overhanging shield finish.

name: Tow Job
description: Short, steep slab with dime edge thin moves.

name: Wet Dreams
description: Good climbing on a blunt arete. Pull on top of the ledge and belay at the Date Bait Sport Anchors and bring up your second.

name: Barn Stormer
description: Start in a nice corner and move past two bolts to a ledge.  Continue up a dihedral to a fractured face of fine brown rock.  Finish by stemming a wide corner to the top anchors.

name: Double Dog Dare
description: Clip the first 3 bolts of Puppy Chow then move right and up.  Continue over a hard bulge clipping 4 more bolts along the way.

name: Lone Ranger
description: Bolt line up a narrow pillar feature left of a large bush.  Climb left of the pillar between the 3rd and 4th bolts then hand traverse right at the 6th bolt to the right side of the pillar.  Follow the corner/bolts to the top anchors.    Original route is rated 11b if stay on the pillar and avoid both corners on either side of the pillar..

name: Puppy Chow
description: Right of Red Shank, climb past 1 bolt to the ledge.  Continue up the face of a column towward a corner system.  Finish at the top anchors in a large roof.

name: Red Shank
description: Follow the line of bolts just right of the large bush about 1/3 the way up the route.      This is the easiest approach pitch to Jail House Wall.  Pull onto the large ledge and walk/scramble 50 feet left to the base of the routes on Jail House Wall.

name: [Redacted]
description: Pull up onto the arete then move slightly left connecting steep pockets to a ramp.  Climb straight up the headwall block to a stance the top anchors.

name: Barbara Dare
description: Climb up the short blocky section of Love Slave. Move right to and up the prox.  Finish left to the top anchors of Love Slave.

name: Bow Wow
description: Fun, sustained for the grade.

name: Boy Toy
description: Several variations.

name: Dawg Daze
description: Tough moves letting up for a cruise to the top.

name: Felix
description: Up a nice face and continue up with nice sections punctuated with small ledges.  This route and Trundler are likely the tallest 5.8's at Massacre where 5.8s are less than 2% of the 750 routes.

name: Girly Mon
description: At the first bolt, most people move left into the short blocky corner, its possible to boulder problem over the first bolt to the ledge.  From the ledge follow a steep right leaning corner.  Finish on pumpy, steep two and three finger pockets.

name: Hollow Weenie
description: White face with thin moves.

name: Immaculate Deception
description: Climb a short thin, fingery corner to a ledge (probably the crux). Continue up hueco'd rock until a big roof.  Pass the roof on the left and gun for the top anchors.

name: Jail Bait
description: Same first 3 bolts as Immaculate Deception then up right leaning dihedral.

name: Kinky
description: Shares a move or two with Love Canal.

name: Lay Back and Enjoy
description: Work through a pumpy flake/bulge about mid-climb.

name: Lip Service
description: Short route left of a blunt prow.

name: Love Canal
description: Stout pockets at the crux.

name: Love Slave
description: Short blocky section leads to great looking right facing dihedral with fun jug hauling on big edges and pockets.

name: Marathon Man
description: Start on slabby brown rock that steepens to a bulge at the top.

name: The Matinee
description: An okay route that starts up a slabby scoop and finishes on some nice pockets.

name: No Hips, Hands, or Butts
description: Thin dihedral start with thin finger jams lead to edges and easier but fun climbing to the top.

name: Paw Prints
description: Short but worthy route starts with a tough pull at the start. The climb eases towards the top.

name: Private Dancer
description: Difficult short, brown prow.

name: Scared Stiff
description: Bolts up brown "hourglass" face, then same finish Slam Bam ...

name: Slam, Bam, Thank You Mam!
description: Blunt arete start.

name: Sweaty Betty
description: Starts on "coral lava" ledge, up overhanging white dihedral on steep and powerful moves.

name: The Tease
description: Route the start between blunt prow and arete to the right.

name: Tension Forever
description: A lttle right of Sweaty Betty, is another bolt line.

name: Thrundler, 5.8
description: Leftmost route on the left side of the Red Light District and approximately at the highest section of the crag.  Steep section and ledges.

name: Tricks Ain't For Kids
description: Excellent thin, technical face.  Hard pull off the ground and stays that way.

name: Twisted
description: Mountaineering flavor with moves punctuated by ledges and deep clefts, upper third is a fun, challenging overhanging dihedral.

name: What A Climb, Max!
description: Tricky moves off the ground, slightly easier than Tricks ...?

name: Woody in the Woods
description: ISU Guide: ***   Crux was near the top of the climb.

name: Axe Cop
description: Same start as Flute Cop, start on block in middle of face with right hand jug and left hand undercling. Throw out right to sidepull crimpy jug and bump to slopey ledge just as you would for Flute Cop. Unlike Flute Cop continue right avoiding large holds out left and the lip, try using the awesome pocket before the lip to help work further right until you are to the end of the boulder and top out on right side.

name: Flute Cop
description: Start on block in middle of the face, right hand on nice jug portion on top right of block and left hand as an undercling. Find a good place for your feet and throw out right to sidepull crimpy jug. Bump right hand out to slopey ledge then work your way up to top out, there are some nice holds out left to help work your way up.

name: Sockarang
description: Start on shoulder height right hand crimp and lower chest height left hand crimp. Work your way out right on small but good holds until you reach larger edges and top out straight up, or veer left for a slightly harder top out.

name: The Picnic
description: Stem and smear your way up this left facing dihedral.

name: Shady Lady
description: Crux start, then engaging moves to the top up a beautiful face.

name: Summer Hummer
description: Sustained and engaging route with a variety of moves to keep things interesting.

name: The Weenie Roast
description: Moderate climbing leads to a powerful crux exiting the roof and guarding the anchors.

name: Charlie Browns Christmas Tree
description: Short problem on jugs. Sit start on far left front side of the boulder where the rock makes a 90+ish degree turn. Start however youd like from sitting and work straight up. One or two moves. Not an amazing route, used to kickoff the start of some boulder development in the area after a long day of sport climbing.

name: Leaning Tree
description: Starts on right side of the front of the boulder. Start on marked start holds (see picture under charlie brown), left hand jug and right hand less of a jug. Work your way left on juggy lip until you reach the section of rock next to charlie brown that is lighter in color then top out. Fairly fun v0.

name: Lumberjack
description: Start as for Snake in my Boot. Again an awkard start for taller people. From the start holds shoot straight up and work your way up the slab directly above. After the first move everything goes as a 0. See picture for Snake in my Boot for line.

name: There's A Snake in My Boot
description: Start on marked start holds, right hand low dirty sidepull and left hand small edge. Feet for the start aren't the best but once you figure them out and pull off avoiding the dab to make the first move up and left staying on the arete the crux is over (dabbing) is over. Continue with one or two more moves using the arete and then work your way into the crimp/side pulls on the face. Work your way left until you can reach the crack on the lip of the boulder and then choose between a few good holds above to find your way to the top. Once again avoid dabbing on the adjacent rock that will be directly behind/below you as you top.

name: Yang
description: Yang follows a light tan band of rock through the apex of the wall.

name: Yen
description: Yen is Japanese currency and Yin is the passive female principle of the universe. Quality movement though.

name: Zen
description: A very boulderer friendly route. The line follows a right leaning arête with great movement. The anchor is two bolts with equalized chains.

name: Bitchin' Widget
description: Good face climbing split by a finger crack. Fingers to ring locks leads to an unprotected bouldery crux. Finish on small hands.

name: Crack-a-Lackin'
description: Dean's description: "One of the best lines at Midget Widget! A thin inside corner crack leads to an overhanging unprotected face. Pull on some good pockets to regain the crack above."

name: Damn the Man
description: Cracks protect some face climbing until you reach thin seams. Protect upper section adequately to prevent falling onto the ledge.

name: Desert Rats Be Damned
description: Short pocketed face protected by hand crack.

name: Finger widget
description: Cool crack, but the route is short. Slightly slanted to the right finger crack that is easy both to climb and protect. Unfortunately once the crack stopped the rock above sounds hollow also chains were not placed higher. Hop onto the same ramp start as widget of oz and middle widget and then climb the crack for about 15 feet.

name: Get Jiggy Widget
description: Inside corner leads to overhanging hands.

name: Got Widgets?
description: Despite the scary mudstone start, this is a fun line! Single bolt protects the bottom. Climb the inside corner to the top of the large flake/block. A cool horizontal finger crack leads right and joins a vertical crack for large hands. Two bolts protect the top.

name: Heavy Metal Widget
description: Mud stone start to a nice inside corner finger crack on bomber stone.

name: Little Widget Big Widget
description: Chains are difficult when walking form the parking lot, but if you walk almost all the way to three piece and turn around, they are obvious. Easy to protect, starts off on smaller gear and each piece you place gets bigger starting from 1.5” to 4”. Super fun and easy.

name: Little Widgets
description: Climb this nice face using positive pockets. Plug gear in the thin crack to the left.

name: Middle Widget
description: To the right of widget of oz. if you have ever looked just to the right and thought that would be a great route, well now it is. Tough climb that starts on a slightly overhung crack that is between hands and fingers. A couple very helpful face holds help get to the big bellow at the top of the crack. Protect before you crawl up into it because there is very limited placement until you start up a little further. After the bellow the crack narrows again and you can climb to chains well protected.

name: Midgets midget
description: Easy to climb easy to protect. Short, would be fun for a beginner to feel safe leading and placing gear.

name: Sport Project 1
description: Sport project.

name: Sport Project 2
description: Sport project.

name: Sport Project 3
description: Sport project.

name: T-Rad
description: Finger crack leads to bulging corner. Strenuous.

name: Three Piece Chicken Widget Meal
description: Start on unprotected but easy, pocketed slab to access the crack. Protect the move pulling onto the protruding block at right. Layback and trust your feet as you ascent this crux move. (A nice pocket on the face makes this move easier.) A large cam or hex protects this fist-width finish.

name: Trad Project
description: Trad project.

name: Why’s everything a widget?
description: First new and different chains you will encounter coming from the parking lot and just to the right of got widgets. Chains are somewhat centered between two cracks, the one on the left is easy to protect until the last 8 or so feet where you must traverse a band of looser rock that can be hard to protect, then clip chains. Gear to 2 inches The crack on the right is a bit wider and while the bottom has some choss, the rest of the route is a lot easier to protect and more centered under the chains. Gear to 2 inches.

name: Wicked Widget of the West
description: Fun and a bit strenuous. Use the inside corner crack and the right face to work up this steep line. Opportunities for gear diminish as you get higher. Fortunately, so does the difficulty.

name: Widget of Oz
description: Can a thirty foot route be described as relentless? Yes, and its name is The Widget of Oz.   The business starts from the first move and doesn't let up until the anchors. Steep, sustained, challenging, and a bit of variation. A great line. Move quickly.

name: Widgets are for Kids
description: Challenging, bouldery start. Protect the roof and pull! Once past the roof, jam fists up a left-trending crack, which then thins to hands and goes straight up. This route shares finish and anchors with God Widgets?

name: Ages of You
description: Very good route.  Stick clip the first bolt, this one gets hard right off the ground.  Mellows out after the first few clips, but another crux awaits on the headwall.

name: King of the Road
description: Significantly easier than the other routes in the Pines. Despite being the warmup, this route requires attention from the start. Challenging for the grade, there are cruxes at the beginning and the end.

name: Toys in the Attic
description: Amazing route!  Starts with a short crux right off the ground, leads to easier climbing and left traversing crack with good holds.  Big rest hold, followed by big move and more hard climbing.

name: [Redacted]
description: Easy to moderate climbing leads to a tricky roof.      Climb over a bulge and angle right up to an orange, right facing dihedral to a tricky roof.

name: Backscratcher
description: Fun climb. Use offwidth, stemming, and wide crack technique to make it up this SPORT route. Protection is great. Wear a helmet!!! You will scuff your head if not careful...and you definitely do not want to take a fall, many places you will hit back of your head...so just wear helmet.

name: Bandwagon
description: Open project. Get after it!

name: Choss Choking Hoss
description: Great power moves right off the deck! 30 feet of sweetened condensed awesome.    Stand on the "cheat block" stone below the first bolt. There is an obvious positive jug to start on. Campus and power through this open book section till you get to the jugs above the second bolt.    Follow the line to a rail and undercling just above the 5th bolt. From here the crux moves up and around the left edge of the bolt line.    Good luck keeping it together for these last powerful moves to jugs and coldshuts!    I skip the 7th bolt.

name: Chupacabra
description: Techy 5.11ish climbing leads to an extremely powerful roof with sharp holds on the headwall.   Probably 5.13a, but I didn't want to be too soft.

name: Easy Street
description: This is a great warmup. the first 30 feet is easy climbing up low angle, golden brown stone, with the steeper crux (5.9+) at the visible chains. The next 15 feet follows two more bolts with a 5.11- move passing the chains ending at cold shuts.

name: Grovel Road
description: Its the two bolt extension of Easy Street. Clip the anchors and continue climbing past a bolt above a ledge...although the bolt is there, don't assume you exit left after Easy Street anchors. Be prepared for a bouldery crux sequence.

name: Hoss, Moss, and Chaos
description: This left to right traversing route is amazing.  Crux is right off the ground.  Make sure to stick clip the first bolt.  This thing hits you with a nasty v6 boulder problem, followed by some 5.11ish climbing to another v5 problem right below the chains.  Classic line!

name: Kaya
description: Starts on slabby featured orange rock...some choss but quality gets better after roof. CLimb to the left of the roof and stand on nice ledge before entering the crux move.

name: Quart of Blood Technique
description: One of the best routes in the area (Weeping Cave).  This is the one with several hanging chain draws.    This route begins just to the left of the pine tree, and means business passing the first bolt. It traverses left after the third bolt, then ascends a left leaning crack/dihedral. It has 2 chain draws on it. you need 6 draws, in addition to the two chain draws, cold shuts for an anchor.

name: Sasquatch
description: This is the furthest right route, that begins up a mellow slab where the trail hits the wall. After the slab there is a small vertical sections ascending a right angling broken crack system to a ledge. After this the crux awaits to cold shut anchors at 10.b

name: Ghost Horse
description: Longest vertical boulder route.

name: Aerial-Fantasy
description: Starts on Aerial Boundaries, but moves right at second bolt. Shares the chains with Aerial Boundaries.

name: Arial Boundaries
description: Cruise to the top.

name: Chuck & Jed's Excellent Adventure
description: Trad climb big inside corner left of Mr. Rodger's. Uses last two bolts and chains of Mr. Rodger's.

name: Dark Side
description: Starts on ledge above and right of Farr Side. Climb face to the right of the leaning crack, then to the left to finish on the same chains as Farr Side.

name: Excitations
description: Clip 2 bolts at bottom, place gear in crack tot he right of Mr. Rodger's, then 2 more bolts on top to chains.

name: Fantasy
description: Starts on loose rock, move up the face, then sidepull the fractured rock to the inside corner left of the pillar.

name: Farr Side
description: Positive holds to ledge with anchors on it.

name: Fly By Night
description: Climb just left of broken arch. Best to do with 60 meter rope.

name: Lower Rainbow
description: Be careful of holds possibly breaking.

name: Mr. Rodger's Neighborhood
description: Climb face just right of Chuck and Jed's to chains.

name: Positively Negative
description: First bolt is up high. 70 meter rope necessary, otherwise double rappel.

name: Spraypaint
description: Mid-way chains make this route more accessible. To mid chains is 5.10b. If going to top 70 meter rope is needed, otherwise it will be 2 rappels.

name: Take the Heise Plunge
description: Overhanging broken arch.

name: Thin Red Line
description: Stay to the right of the bolt line until third bolt, then move to the left onto the face, then straight up.

name: Wild Thing
description: Use cracks to the right of Excitations.

name: [Redacted]
description: Juggy opening moves lead to a delicate open book. Difficult stemming and endurance will take you to the anchors.

name: American Gladiator
description: 5.9ish moves lead to a difficult crux around the 3rd and 4th bolts. Pull around the roof to a large rest ledge, then slippery 5.7 to the anchors.

name: Anchored to the Sky
description: Climb a broken column with a large rest ledge in the middle.

name: Cure for the Hangover
description: Fun vertical climbing on good holds. traverse left to avoid the roof, then back right to the anchors.

name: I’m Too Sexy for My Lycra
description: Climb column to smooth open book, over the lip to steep finish at anchors.

name: Predicaligament
description: Just right of Lycra, this route climbs it’s way up to the wide dihedral with a crack in it all the way to the anchors.

name: tequila hangover
description: climb 'cure for the hangover' (5.9) to just below the roof. head straight out the roof to a glued-on hold. head up and a bit left if you can reach, then top out on easy moves.

name: Tequila Sunrise
description: Columns to bulbous section, then up through bulge and finish on hidden jugs.

name: Toejam
description: Start up the broken face to fun moves in a small corner and left to anchors.

name: UNNAMED
description: Next to toejam, this route starts in white column section up to a small ledge and finishes on a short, steep face.

name: Yo Mama
description: Crux chimney start, cruise to top tope anchors.

name: Gas station grass
description: Super fun boulder I figured out while filling up gas when I was driving through town, it was pretty dirty with lots of lichen on the rock so I have no idea if it’s really been done before.        use the obvious double and mono pockets as starts with both feet out right, one foot on the small diagonal ledge. Move across the series of good crimps to a small jug on your upper left. From the small jug reach over the edge for a good hold to pull on to top out.

name: Beer Goggles
description: Stand start with left hand flat edge and right hand crimp on face around chest height. Work your way onto the upper slab with balancy moves on good rock. A harder sit start could be added.

name: Corner Pocket
description: Short problem on an adjacent boulder from the bar stool. This problem can be seen lookers left of Beer Goggles.  Start low and left in a good mail slot. Using intermediate slopers, to gain the pocket. Easy mantle.  Down climb as for Beer Goggles

name: Gravity Storm
description: Sit start at the bottom of the cave with a left hand under cling at lip of the cave and a right side pull. Hit a square jug and move right to a sloper to a jug. easy top out. Easy top out.

name: On the Rocks
description: Sit start at the bottom of the cave  with a left hand under cling at lip of the cave and a right side pull. Hit a square jug and move left to a side pull crimp. Crux revolves around hitting a slope before the lip. Easy top out. Gravity Storm shares the same start and first few moves.

name: Blofeld
description: Starts on good undercling for left hand and flat ledge for right hand.  Move big to jug ledge and try hard out left or hard straight up.  Finish in center of wall.

name: Felix Lighter
description: Start on two good crimps on low left side of face. Move out right and up to meet the top-out of Moneypenny.

name: Felix Lighter (sit)
description: This is a sit start to the existing problem Felix Lighter V5. Sit start as low as possible in the overhang. Left hand on a slopey side pull and Right hand on the lowest side pull rail in the position most comfortable. Bump the right hand to a good side pull in a awkward position, throw a left heel hook and do a big left cross into the start of the original line. I had a big swing to get established and the move will vary with height.   The original line: From two crimps at mid height, hit a small pocket. With a surprisingly good heel hook pull the lip and top out straight up.   The other beta says to go into Moneypenny but that seems less straightforward.

name: Goldfinger
description: Hopefully you have stronger tendons than I did. Stand start on a left two finger pinch and a quarter pad crimp. Technical mantle.

name: James Bond
description: Start low and right on two bad crimps and move right and up over the lip to a tricky slab top-out.

name: James Penny
description: Start on James Bond. Once you hit the holds at the lip, make a big move to the left and finish on Moneypenny.

name: Mission Improbable
description: Sit start right of James Bond on pocket side-pull and crack system.  Move up face to fierce in-cut crimp out left, and slap sloper to a decent horizontal jug-dish in the center of the face.  Top out just right of James Bond on decent gaston and mostly imaginary feet.

name: Moneypenny
description: Stand start on jug right of the crack.  Find feet and move up the crack to a good top-out.

name: Skyfall
description: Stand start on a good rail at head height. Climb the arete topping out on the left side.

name: Sweet Honey Rider
description: Start in a good horizontal slot, followed by a thin crack.

name: Thunderball
description: Stand start in a horizontal at chest level. Climb the face.  Brush your ticks!

name: Tomorrow Never Dies
description: Bear hug the overhanging arête. After pulling the lip the problem gets easier.

name: Try Another Day
description: Hopefully the start hold will stay. Throw into a under cling to thin face moves.

name: Albi's Undercling
description: Start on jug undercling on right side of boulder and go straight up.

name: Lockin-OffTheTopOfThis-Esophagus
description: Starts low in a crack close to the ground and makes a couple hard moves to the lip and up.

name: Perkins' Slab AKA The Bearded Leslie
description: Climb the slab right around the corner of Thaller Traverse. In this case I took the liberty to name a problem after my closest friend.

name: The Thaller Traverse AKA Andrew's Lady Fingers
description: Okay I really just wanted to name a problem after me, it is ego but have free reign to call it whatever you want. Oliver will likely have many names I'm sure. Start low on the right leaning crack and traverse the crack through a two-finger pocket, continue through the crack to the end and top out.

name: Hope Floats
description: The most logical start for me was to have left hand under cling on a pinch and right hand on a lower crimp. Bad feet under the roof and try not to dab.

name: El Conquistador
description: Stand start in the middle of the face with two small under cling crimps. The crux revolves around matching a 1/4 crimp rail to a moderate top out. I did the line originally using some holds Xibalba, this is a fun variation and about the same in grade.

name: El Dorado
description: Start low lying back; straight up moving right at the top out.

name: Sacrificial Altar
description: Stand start follow the rail to  a delicate top out.

name: Spicy Hot Coco
description: Stand start in pockets, up the arete

name: Xibalba
description: (Chi Ball Ba) Sit Start on a big pinch short and powerful.

name: Akhenaten
description: The obvious overhanging arete! Start low with a good edge for the left hand and a sharp square crimp for the right. Make powerful moves to good edges at the lip and commit into the recess above. From here, turn around and jump down. The topout may go with a lot of cleaning but the fall would be bad if you don't make it.

name: Eye of Horus
description: Sit start with a left hand crimp and right hand on the bubbly eye hold. Big move to  a small pitch, pull the lip and traverse right to the ledge. Leave a pad to jump off the ledge.

name: Journey to the Afterlife
description: Sit start using large sidepull on arete. Make a couple of moves using good holds until you establish on the slab arete. Use small crimps and a monopocket to smear feet and commit high to a good flat edge. This is also the downclimb, so a spotter and some pads below are recommended!

name: King Tut
description: Stand start matched on a good sloping side pull. Laybacks to a crux at the lip to a ledge then climb down.

name: Duality AKA Green Toe
description: Start low on small crimps. The line continues straight.

name: Moonstone
description: Sit start on a crescent moon crimp. Throw to a left sloper gaining a under cling crimp. Either cross or bump to a nice incut crimp. Top out on a nice flat lip.

name: Dharma Daze
description: Stand start on slopey edges, the line follows the arete to a good top out. Landing is not the best.

name: Ganesh
description: Start on opposing side pulls. Reach high to a crimpy under cling, followed by a big move to a crimp. Acrobatic footwork to gain the arete leads to a delicate top out.

name: Hanuman
description: This technical slab is one worthy of the Monkey God. Start low toward the left side of the boulder under a roof. Follow the slab on good edges to a sloper top out.

name: Kama Sutra
description: Start low following a good side pull to the white varnished arete.

name: Ravana
description: Follow a hand crack to a thin lay back. Avoid exiting out left, where the crack widens.

name: Shiva the Destroyer
description: Start low with a left two finger pocket and right crimp on the arete. Navigate through shallow huecos to a fun face.

name: Kamaloso
description: Sit start low on the arete. Follow the arete left to the apex using some edges on the face.

name: Odin's Arete
description: Best V0 in the Park. Follow jugs up the face to delicate huecos. Either exit right toward Valhalla on good holds.

name: Odin's Arete Direct
description: Follow jugs up the face to delicate huecos to a dicey top out.

name: Skål
description: Sit start with a left gaston and a right pinch. Big moves on good holds.

name: Ulfberht
description: A surprisingly hard slab. Stand start on holds around chest level, follow sloping edges to an awkward top out.

name: Valhalla
description: Jump start to slopers. Match onto a decent rail, moving right into a gaston. If you do not say “TO VALHALLA!” prior to your attempt the Nordic Gods will not grant you a send.

name: Apollo
description: Compression test piece of the area. Sit start left hand low and a right hand on a good flat edge. For me I found it easier to cross left hand to a good incut and bump the right hand to a pinch above the incut. Then move left and start compressing. The crux is throwing right hand to the lip. To moderate top out.  Disclaimer: The hold you throw to on the lip broke in half on the FA and I foresee it breaking entirely in the future. In the spirit of that I did the line again using a 1/4 pad crimp slightly left of the original hold.   I think if you use the original, it's probably V7. New way V8.

name: Fig Leaf
description: For those who value decency, this is a great choice. Start laybacking a sloper, work into a separation on the arete. Finish on the apex of the boulder.

name: Wedding Tackle
description: Decency is out the window to send. Sit start with a left sloper and a low right-hand jug. A hard move to gain the left leaning arete. Finish the same as Fig Leaf.

name: Closer to the Sun
description: Stand start LH at head height on a 1/2 pad down pull crimp, RH low on a sloper side pull. Pull the bulge on crimps and a hidden small pocket. Easy top out.

name: Icarus
description: Start on opposing gaston crimps, this is an excellent judge of footwork and finger strength. Top out on good holds.

name: Forge from Fire
description: Sit start with a left under cling and right-hand crimp. Crux is pulling the lip, continue up arete to top out.

name: Fuego
description: Stand start follow the crack to a fun mantle.

name: Torched
description: Sit start with left hand on sloper and right hand low side pull on the arete created by the huge split in the boulders. Straight up and mantle over the large ledge. Short but fun!

name: Aphrodite
description: Start low on wild pockets, then pull the lip to easier terrain. The problem also serves as the downclimb.

name: Julius Seizure
description: A burly roof that climbs like a chimney. Start low in the cave on a positive rail, follow the rail through torturous body positions on slopers. The finale, involves creative movement cutting right, matching a side pull pinch into Aphrodite.   The direct finish follows a line of crimps  into a sharp two finger crimp to a separate top out.

name: Triumvirate
description: Stand start with a high left hand crimp/mini pinch. Follow an easier crack system, trend left to a flat jug and pull a small lip. The top sequence has a 1/4 pad gaston and a slopey finish. The key feet at the top need more cleaning at this time.

name: When in Rome
description: A fantastic highball. Stand start with a high left crimp and balance with the right. Easy movement on small edges leads to a high crux transferring right to a jug. Top out maybe dirty but is on good holds.

name: Cerberus
description: Using the same start as Underworld, traverse right on small holds until gaining the right arete. Head left to the apex to top out.

name: Underworld
description: Sit start on a left leaning side pull. Using the arete head right to the apex of the boulder to an easy top out.

name: Hoplite
description: Left hand side pull and a right-side pull. A big move to a crimp.

name: Lino Thorax
description: The line follows the right leaning arete. Low start with a right-hand side pull.

name: Phalanx
description: Sit Start in a slopey hueco and move through the eyeball huecos. Cool holds, but short.

name: Achaean Deception
description: Start at the bottom left with two thin crimps on the overhanging lip. Traverse right on the lip with good holds and heel hooks, finish on low angle slab.

name: Achilles Heel
description: Start low on the left trending rail following flat edges to an exciting finish.

name: Kleos: Glory in War
description: Start low with opposing side pulls, the right being the better hold. Following a foot ramp to the left, many ways exist to enter the top section. After the hardest moves, There is a section where you can rest and finish into the V4 slab. Finish to the top of the boulder, tall finish on low angle easy climbing.

name: Styx
description: Sit start with a left hand side pull and a horizontal pocket for the right under an small roof. Big moves and a tricky mantel. Topping the boulder is easy slab climbing, or jump off after the mantle.

name: Bowser Jr
description: Stand start with a large left pitch on the arete and a right side pull on the face. Set up the feet and jump to the lip.

name: Bowser’s Chokehold
description: Sit start with a left under cling pinch and a right hand on a slot. Tackle the arete through slopers and crimps. Moderate top out.

name: Eyerok
description: Sit start on opposing side-pulls to a triangle pinch, then gain the sloper to head left on a tricky mantle.

name: Goomba Superslam
description: Sit start LH on a small crimp RH on a good edge. Compression moves to gain the lip. Short and sweet.

name: Koopa Troopa Slab
description: A fun slab on the east face stand start.

name: Koopa Troopa Slab (low)
description: Start just to the right of the KTS start on a right leaning jug in the roof. Pull onto a set of three half pad crimps and traverse into the stand.

name: Whomp King
description: Daniel knows firsthand what the name means, as a hundred-pound boulder fell on him when attempting the sit start. Stand start with a high right-hand crimp and left side pull. This climb also acts as the downclimb. The sit start will also go.

name: Yoshi
description: Sit start pull through a roof. This small boulder is adjacent to the Goomba on the NW corner.

name: Devil in the Details
description: Start on a sloper around chest height. Thin technical moves.

name: Pit of Hell
description: Sit start with a juggy side pull to a good crimp. Techy mantle.

name: Satan's Alley
description: Sit start low on crimps, then move left into Pit of Hell.

name: Tea Box
description: Match a good under cling and follow crimps straight up.

name: Tidal Pool
description: Stand start matched on right facing crack side-pull.  Move right and up around the arete to an easy top-out.

name: Tsunami
description: Start left hand on low jug side-pull and right hand on high sloping side-pull.  Move up and left, rearange feet, and mantle over.

name: I’d Rather be Jammin
description: Sit start on a low jug rail. Slightly contrived start to another good jug rail. Hand jam, dead point off the jam. Pause on a finger lock to the top. Inevitably you will likely dab a branch which takes a star away. Landing is okay with 3 pads but also loses a star for the landing.

name: King Animal
description: Stand start LH undercling RH on a sharp crimp in the bubbly rock about head height gain a heel hook and punch up incut edges to an easy slab.

name: Natural Element
description: Cool traverse and compression rail line with some dab potential at the start.Sit start on the left arete. Climb up the arete to a jug without dabbing. Move right to a matchable crimp in the center face. Gain the right arete and use slopers on the rail to a dynamic finish.

name: Land of the Lost
description: Stand start low on crimps. Delicate moves on crimps to a dead point.

name: Madre Mia
description: Stand Start LH on a bad crimp chest height and RH on a better crimp. Big move to a crimp rail, hard match, hard move pulling the lip.

name: Mama Tried
description: Thin edges with a committing move near the top. Landing is less than ideal but is a fun problem to test the mind.

name: Mother's Little Helper
description: Start with flat jug and fingerlock/ringlock undercling in corner. Use sharp crimps and pockets in the seam to establish onto the upper face. Top out with easier climbing above.

name: Mother's Milk
description: Hard crimping down low to a juggy finish.

name: Arte Suave
description: Sit start on flat edge and undercling. Follow sidepulls and edges up the left arete to moderate topout.

name: Bushido Code
description: Stand start with the two jugs at about shoulder height. Use thin crimps on the face with good edges for feet until you can reach the jug above the slab. Topout direct or slightly left.

name: Foot Fist Way
description: Sit start with both hands on the obvious good hold. Pull on and make a move right, then follow crimps and edges that face the wrong way up the low angle corner.

name: Kung Fu Grip
description: Start with two hands on the flat ledge. Use creative footwork to obtain a series of pinches, edges and sidepulls. Topout direct.

name: Space Force
description: Sit start LH on a full pad crimp, RH on a fat pinch. Go straight up using a variety of holds. Dirty top out.

name: Stellar Abyss
description: Stand start on the arete and a right-hand side pull, follow thin moves to a large hole with an engaging top out.

name: 2 minute man
description: Start on good hold on the right side of boulder.  Grab big pockets to the top.  Super short

name: Capital Punishment
description: SDS: move left off of a small RH side pull and blind feet. Easy top out

name: Chub
description: Start on obvious jug.  Make your way up pockets to a mantle.     Shorty but goody

name: Flow
description: Sit Start in a small pocket and a right side pull. Move up the arête to a good top out.

name: Mile High Club (MHC)
description: This was a hell of a project to finish up. Many sessions, many trips over a year of effort. Sit start on a flat edge, with a bad heel. The majority of the climb feels like your doing a hollow body while being punched with V8 moves to a low percentage move. Easy top out.

name: Mile High Club Stand AKA The Half Mile
description: Less of a stand and more of the higher start. LH on the good sloper, RH under cling. Big move to a crimp rail, weird heel, and power to a full pad crimp. Final easy boulder problem to an easy top out.

name: Pain and Gain
description: Never actually done them, let me know what you think. And the First Ascentionist doesn't know.

name: Red Eye Flight
description: Start on a slopping edge and do a big move to a jug.

name: Sage
description: Sit start with right hand on good sloper arete and left hand on bad sloper around the corner.  Use good ramp for feet and throw up to good hold.  Move around left, making use of the good ramp foot, to an easy top out.

name: Skittles
description: Start on the far left of the boulder and slap up the rail with good feet.  Find good holds at the top point of the boulder, get higher feet, and do a "swimming pool" mantle.  Foot ramp is off at the far right side of the boulder

name: That's Compressive
description: Stand start on left crimp and right undercling.  Compress your way up to a good pinch out right and make your way to the top out.

name: Captain Crunch
description: See photo. I haven't done it.

name: Death Card
description: Compression start under the roof. Throw left to a good crimp, slap the flat jug and move left into a juggy rail. Follow the rail back right to top out.

name: Death Card (sit)
description: Sit start on opposing crimps. The RH being the better of the two in the green lichen. Hard move to a sloper gaston. Match and work into the stand.

name: Dropout
description: I haven't been on it, Preston said sit start.

name: The Executioner
description: Haven't been on this, Preston said this was his favorite he put up at Massacre.

name: Honest John
description: Stand start avoiding the ledge out right.

name: Lorenzini's Roof
description: Sit start. Follow good edges into Death Card.

name: Slap Happy
description: Haven't done it.

name: Prognosis
description: Start with opposing two side-pull crimps, pull past some crimps to good holds.  Good Top-out

name: Pythagorean
description: Start on obvious slots.  Smear feet and move up left to diagnoal crimp.  Easy top out.   Arete is out.

name: Pythagorean Left
description: Start in obvious slots; same start as Pythagorean, but slap up left on arete to the tip of the boulder to top out.

name: Venom Crack
description: Stand start with a left hand in the crack and a right hand around the corner. Work you way up the crack with some bad feet and strenuous movement.

name: Reach
description: Sit start on giant undercling. Use crack and reach up to crimp to an easy top out.  Arete is out.

name: Reach-No hands (aka Douche Canoe)
description: Yes this is a douche-bag route, but I promise... you will have fun.    Use only high foot on "Reach" and jump up to the hidden jug to top out.

name: Roll the Dice
description: Start on a jug on the left side and compress to the top. Feels easy to bail left into the cracks, but it’s worth stays on the compression.

name: Highwayman
description: A pretty arete overlooking the highway. Start with a small pocket and a sloper. Follow the arete to a mantle.

name: Dragon Skin
description: The problem sits in a small cove with and is approached by down climbing from the upper tier. The problem also required 5 stacked pads to level the landing zone. Start low on opposing holds, continue straight up to a top out on pockets.

name: Green Mamba
description: Beautiful scenery and a pretty face. Green Mamba starts in a hole on a flake. Climb out of the hole and traverse right onto the left leaning arete. Feels like a gym problem.

name: New Fang
description: Same start as Green Mamba. Serious dab potential, but the line is okay while you’re there. Instead of traversing right as for Green Mamba, go straight up on good slopers. Easy top out.

name: Ophis
description: Another short problem starting on the left arete of the North face of the boulder. Sit start on a small platform on crimps traverse up and right into New Fang. Decent climb but not note worthy

name: Shredded Chedda
description: Sit start on right side pull and an option of a hidden mono-undercling or a small crimp out left.  Find feet and move up to a fantastic jug for a cool mantle.

name: RhinoVirus
description: Double Undercling start to Big Moves to good holds and an easy top out.

name: Spinal Tap
description: Start on spine down low.  Work you feet and pull on good holds veering left to a tricky top out.  You can top out straight up or to the left; both are tricky.

name: Queen of the Rodeo
description: Sit start into a small pocket.

name: The Wrangler
description: Start on the jug at the bottom right with two hands. Minimal feet at the start. Move left up the rail. Massive left foot rest before going straight up to top out.

name: Brianstorm
description: Follow a overhang out left on good holds.   The rock quality looks bad, but is surprisingly amazing.

name: Diamonds Are Forever
description: Low start on the right side of The Cube, around the corner from Rubix L-R. Finish out right

name: Double Decker
description: A two part climb, involving a Slabby V0 and a traverse V0. To start Slabby start on the right side on a good right hand jug and move up and left. Top out to the traverse, strating on the left side in a good pocket and move right.

name: Fins and Tails
description: Start on the left side gain a foot on the small ledge, and finish right.

name: Green Green Under Green
description: Start standing directly in the middle of the Big Boy boulder on crimps and finish up Money Plays.

name: Heelhooks and Hookers
description: Start low and begin to move left using heel hooks, top out left.

name: Money Plays
description: Left most line the  Big Boy boulder. Sit Start on a good edge and finish straight up.

name: Mountaineer's Boulder
description: Easy almost a scramble.

name: Plexiglass
description: Fun little slab

name: Rebirth
description: Start in a small cave on a undercling and work your way out top out direct.

name: Rubix L
description: On the Cube Boulder, start on the left side wall and heel to gain a jug.

name: Rubix R
description: Same as Rubix L except you start on the Right side of the wall.

name: Slice of Life
description: Start on Twist of Cain, grab the sloper. From here match and traverse into Green Green Under Green to the top.

name: Squeeze
description: Use the side pull on Twist Of Cain and a right hand side pull to work your way up the Big Boy Boulder.    Bring an ape index, it's height dependent.

name: Squeeze Less
description: A variation of Squeeze starting on a nice jug, allowing those without a long ape index to climb it.

name: Stairmaster
description: Traverse right starting on a the top left corner around the whole boulder, then top out.

name: Stolen Chimnmini
description: Start on low crimps and stay left avoiding the right wall. Cool arete climb with a top out resembling Stolen Chimney in Moab.

name: Teddy Picker
description: Sit start right of Brianstorm, passed the bush. move left then top out right. Watch for Cactus.

name: Twist Of Cain
description: Start low with a good undercling and a right hand side pull. Work your way up this overhanging beauty.

name: Evil Petting Zoo
description: Sit start on the back of a small cave. Left hand on a good edge and right in a hueco feature. Climb the arete through perfect edges and creative movement. Top out on good knobs but campusy movement.

name: Zoo York
description: Awkward start to a slopey finish.

name: Albatross Traverse
description: Start on Private Property and end on the No Trespassing boulder. A knee bar funky beta and a huge move off a sloping side pull to a jug. This problem will have you wishing for a bigger ape index.    For more climbtastic fun finish up on Trespassing Gets You Killed V3

name: No Treaspassing
description: A small compression problem right of the No Trespassing painted sign. Avoid the features off to the right.

name: Private Property
description: left most route in the No Trespassing area, it is the first thing you see from the road.

name: Property Line
description: Pretty much the same as Private Property, it starts in the dihedral to the right. Later join the same finish.

name: Rip Curl
description: Start matching a undercling in the middle of the No Trespassing wall, shared with Fallen Horehound. move up and right following a small arête to gain a sharp two finger stack. Finish on Trespassing gets you killed.

name: Sendasaurus Rex
description: Named for the plant that will stick to your pads, a problem that originally had a 3 foot long flake. this flake is gone now creating a hard undercling start. Follow the line up good edges and creative footwork, for a final throw for the lip.

name: Trespassing Gets You Killed
description: So many cool moves!! Start on a sloping rail, and work your way up the crack. Move left and grab a side pull, set into a knee bar to grab a good edge. Spicy finish but safe falls.

name: Band From Idaho
description: A crack route right of a prominent arête, takes good gear.

name: Bear Grab
description: A shorter version of Sangre. Start low directly below the mantle jug. Grab some crimpy pinches and finish the same as Sangre.

name: The Bengali
description: A blunt arête around the corner from Kamehameha Roof. Start on a good jug and piece the moves together, until gaining a ledge about half way up. Finish on easier ground, but probably shouldn't fall.

name: Covid Crack
description: Left hand start in the bottom crack right hand start on out of the furnace arête. Work your way up the crack while using the occasional face holds. TOP OUT

name: Dragonfly Tattoo
description: Start low cave on a undercling, move left into a two-finger crimp. Reach a right hand gaston, with some tricky footwork obtain a left hand crimp to top out. Left wall is off.

name: Famous Potatoes
description: A blunt arête. Sit start and move into a perfect crimp, follow some compression moves with a 2 finger pocket. A spicy move at the top, move right for the top out

name: The Illusionist
description: Another new one, opened by the tree incident. It follows a left leaning crack to meet up at the same top out as Punji Spikes.

name: Kamehameha Roof
description: Short wide crack. Scramble up to the crack layback to a jug at the lip, pull the roof to some good jams.

name: Knees on Wheels
description: A line to the right of Oreo Blaster. Start on good holds and slap up right through slopey side pulls. Bring the feet up on Oreo Blaster's ledge and continue up the dihedral. A knee bar may help.

name: Lion's Den
description: This line fills the gap between Tumble In The Weeds and Sangre. Start on the Sangre jug and move left into Tumble. Cool moves not a bad line.

name: Loss Of Control
description: Keep your head on for this one. Start low on an under cling, moving into good edges and jugs. The crux involves moving past a good under cling, obtaining a shelf and dead pointing to a jug. This mark the half way point. It is V1 to the top, however it is no gimme.     The wall to the left and crack is off and it climbs strait up the face.

name: Oreo Blaster
description: Starts in a small cave, it goes up through a distinct blast hole.

name: Out of the Furnace
description: Start low on a juggy sloper and a right hand side pull. Work your way up the aesthetic arête.

name: Panda Watch!
description: right of the Famous Potatoes arête up a depression in the face. Up jugs the same top out.

name: Punji Spikes
description: A recent route due to someone poorly chopping a tree. This line feels like committing 5.6 and your pads will be covering deathly spikes until we remove the tree completely.

name: Sagre Del Tigre
description: Jug start move right up some slapping moves. Moves into a hard compression move to a dyno. Mantle to a easy top section.

name: Salamander Send Off
description: Stand start under this prominent arete right of the cave. The line leads into small dihedral to a mid height crux. The top is techy but easier, to set up a TR ; single set of cams  .5 to 2

name: Sangre Directo
description: The direct line to Sangre Del Tigre and a great addition to the Tumbleweeds. Start low in the cave on a jug, compression climbing under a roof leads to a hard transition at the lip. Easy top out.

name: Senorita
description: A bold highball. The line start at the far right side of the main cave, following the overhanging arête pulling onto the face. Small holds on the face follow the path of least resistance up the face.

name: Svety Balls
description: Below the mantle. Sit start move into a big pinch to a big move to a jug, may be height dependent.

name: Tumble In The Weeds
description: Start low in the cave, grab a right hand side pull to a cool cross to a slopper. Finish out left or straight up.

name: Bell Pepper
description: Left of Pineapple Dreams in a corner. Climb the face avoiding the corner. Short and slabby.

name: Blue Juice
description: Start on a rectangular edge, move up on small edges. obtain the ledge. You can top out here, but for the full quality avoid topping out on the ledge and move left. Go straight up into a triangle shaped jug.

name: Get on the Boat!
description: Short and sweet on a floating boulder. Start matched on a sloper, with a double toe hook. Slap up the arete to a good jug at the top. I needed a small mono however a taller person may have an easier time. (I’m 5.11-plus 1 ape index)

name: Paradise
description: Sit Start on a right hand broken flake, move up to some good ledges.

name: Pineapple Dreams
description: A great highball, Start with a heel-toe cam and two good crimps. Continue up the face avoiding the side walls for full the value.

name: Back Scratch Fever
description: A small outcropping boulder surrounded by cracks. Start low on the right side, and move up and left. You can traverse all the way left making it easier. For the full value top out the boulder direct, however be warned a bush sits on top that is the problems name sake. Walk off to the left.

name: Innocent Minds
description: One of the last great high balls at the Tumbleweeds. Dirty bottom with easy face climbing to a techyy dihedral, avoid resting on the ledge out left. I worked it on a rope before the send so the grade is anywhere from V4 to V6. Even so this is engaging at the top, and a great highball.

name: Midday Swerve
description: Sit Start on a juggy side pull head up the arête on crimps to a techy mantle. Exit left to a down climb.

name: Secret Tickle Time
description: Hand traverse into the hands crack. Secure climbing easy top out. Highball

name: The Bandolier
description: Start on a mail slot about chest height. Work your way up and right through the arête, until gaining a big pocket. Topping out direct from here is doable, but it is much safer to continue right on the top of Dancing Shoes.

name: Barefoot Ballerina
description: A Dyno variation of Dancing Shoes V0. See Beta photo. Great dyno to a huge jug.

name: Cherry
description: A small roof leads into horizontal pockets and a hand jam at the top. The top out is the crux and should not be take lightly. Grab the top slopper and mantle over.

name: Dancing Shoes
description: The farthest right climb at the Tumbleweeds. Start on a big jug and layback the crack, to a very positive top out. A good beginner climb!

name: Flying Blind
description: The problem goes up the slab to the right of Cherry and moves left into a crack. The problem has a bit of a blind move hence the name.

name: Indian Summer
description: Start on good side-pulls to a flat ledge. Work into a small finger crack to the top out.

name: Snake Bite
description: A variation of The Bandolier, avoiding the arête and staying on the south facing wall. Start low on a rail, continue up sharp crimps with good feet then a dead point to a slightly larger crimp. Once you get the big pocket top out the same as the Bandolier.

name: The X rated
description: Easy but unprotected, and sharp rocks at the bottom. Start on a flake at waist height, move up to a big undercling to top out.

name: Black Hook
description: Start with a heel hook and match and good rail.

name: Firehouse
description: On the west face of the boulder and left of a small juniper tree. Start on to good edges and heel hook in a depression hidden by the juniper.

name: Ghost Hands
description: This route is in a small cave right of Firehouse. ROOF CRACK!!! Just when you think the Tumbleweeds couldn't get any better, it brings you a roof crack. No jams just lay backs and foot jams.

name: Animal Parts
description: Start in a small hueco and follow the line straight up hidden cracks.

name: Bullrider
description: Start the same as Elephant Ear. Follow a thin seam up delicate crimps, throw out right to a jug and top out direct. Heady top out be careful. Avoid the holds left of the seam.

name: Chicken Of The Sea
description: Start in a horizontal down low and follow the line through cool pockets to a good top out.

name: Elephant Ear
description: Start on a outcropping hold and follow a leftward leaning crack to a decent top out.

name: Flamingos Eat Hippo
description: On the Elephant Ear feature there is a pinch near the top right hand corner. Start on the pinch and move up the slab to a sloppy crimp. From here enter the crux. Top out left or right both are up there in the sky.

name: Fly Like A Pelican (Sting Like Your Mutha)
description: Start on a left hand pinch and a right crimp. Throw right to a large block then left to a good pinch. A hand foot match allowed me to move up to a sharp tooth shaped crimp. From here dyno to a good side pull, these leads to a delicate top out.

name: Ivy League
description: A dramatic overhang on the far right of the east wall, by Moss Infection. I built a landing zone for the climb and will admit it can be improved upon. Start low on good under clings, through side pulls to the crux. About midway there is a jug, from this point you may bail or continue for 3 moves to the top out. NOTE the top out is potentially dangerous.

name: Monkey Circus Freak
description: A well defined crack right of Fly Like A Pelican

name: Moss Infection
description: A traversing rail on the west facing wall. Sit start with a left hand crimp and a right sloper.

name: Silverback Grip Pump
description: Starting low in the cave move out into a pinch rail, work up to a thin crack. Finish has good holds bad feet. Definitely inspect the top out.

name: Cyclops
description: Start with a side pull and move into a good horizontal. Straight up to a three finger pocket to top out.

name: Fins
description: Reminiscent of climbing in the Fins. Start low on a good ledge and move up through varied pockets. Move right to a good edge and bump to a undercling to top out.

name: Polaris
description: Good climbing crappy landing. See beta photo for details.

name: Young, Wet and Overhung
description: The north most climb up a cool overhang. Start on good edges  and move through pockets and side pulls.

name: Bushwhacking
description: Ok so this is the first route on the left, however trudging through some bush is involved. After reaching the landing area, there is enough space for a pad and one to protect the rock behind. Good jugs and fun moves, but short. Variation would be skipping the left crack system (V5) up a half pad crimp.

name: Culture Of Silence
description: Start on two side pull crimps to a left hand sloppy jug. Obtain a right hand side pull and go for the lip.

name: Pharaoh
description: Sit start with a left hand undercling and a right hand side pull, throw up right to a full pad crimp and slap with the left. Gain the horizontal, and set up left on a pinch under cling. Work your feet up and do a dynamic move to the lip.

name: The Angle
description: Start to the right of Your Answer... on a big right facing jug work right through big moves on good holds until you get out of the cove. Look for a pad sized sloper-crimp with your right hand and move onto the face and go for the small sharp knife blades with your left. Move up and right to better hold to top out.

name: Bull Snake
description: Sit start on side rail of crack, hand jam or lay back to a whopping jug and top out.

name: Classic (Black Beard)
description: Short but Sweet! Same start as Small Dyno... But once you reach the top of the sloping rail, go straight up with a good side pull some to cambering and a grovelling top out.

name: Detox Simulator
description: Start on good holds move straight up to an undercling with your right hand and catch a sloping rail with your left. Matching the rail move up and left to a really sharp half pad two finger pocket with your left hand and cross through to bad crimp with your right enter the Angle's crimps and exit left on good but sloping holds.

name: Drop Knee Gorgeous
description: Sit start on the right side of the Project bulge and move up and right to a left hand gaston and right hand side pull and a good foot(start of T.E.L.P). Move up and left to a good side pull and horizontal crimp. Up and left to the top.

name: The Flight
description: Same start as Detox... but just go straight up. Big move off the sloping rail to a shallow pod with your right hand and gun for the V notch up and left. I had to use a heel hook to make the move. Desperate and scary.

name: Josh's Problem
description: Start at the left side of the cove climb big holds up and left to the top

name: Jug-A-Haulic
description: Start on left facing jug side-pull and and go up utilizing cracks and a big block out left.

name: Pinky Pain
description: Same start as Detox and the Flight, but after the right hand undercling you can pinky-lock your left hand in a notch and throw for a right facing rail. Then up and right

name: Pot Belly
description: Stand start under the belly on opposing side-pulls and work up the Buddha using a crimp and slopers towards the top. Great problem!

name: Project...
description: The software made me rate it. My guess; having worked the problem, getting extremely close to finishing it, and my bouldering pursuits to the south this winter - I feel it will go around V11 or 12 who knows and/or really cares.     Sit start with good left hand side-pull and move up and left over a bulged belly through some really small crimps to finish the same as Zoro.

name: Small Dyno in a Big World
description: Sit start on two really good in-cut holds move up and left using a nice sloping rail. Move left hand out to a sloper around the corner, feet up and gun for the lip.

name: T.E.L.P
description: Sit start on big side rail and move up crack with ring locks to jug.

name: The Vulcan
description: Stand start with right hand under cling and make a long move up to a left hand pocket that splits your fingers into the "vulcan" sign! Stabilize with a quarter pad 1 1/2 finger pod with right hand and a big move to deceivingly poor side pull. Top to jug.

name: You've Got Mail
description: Same start as Classic and Small Dyno.. But move up and right to a huge mail slot to a slopey top out.

name: Your Answer, My Answer, and the Truth
description: Start just to the right of Josh's problem on big jug and go straight up and out the cove on big holds with big moves to some big flakes at the top

name: Zoro
description: The name is purposefully spelled with one "R" due to the fact that the original 1957 TV series "Zorro" was so good that everything else doesn't deserve the 2nd! Start left hand on a good side pull 2 inches from Vulcan's under cling start. Put right hand on a good edge (pick one of many). Make a big move right to a sloper. Move left foot up by the start hold and press up and left to get your left finger in the pod that is shared with the Vulcan. When the mono is attained make a dynamic move up and right to a jug, good holds to top-out.

name: 11 O'clock
description: A little balance will help with this one. Some deceptive moves in the latter half. Follow the bolt line pretty much straight up.

name: 4-Alarm Fire
description: Slightly overhanging, traverse below the roof at the start to access first bolt. Use caution as a fall here would be unfortunate. Pull straight up for a few moves to a right-leaning rail. Look for pockets on the face and climb a few more bolts.

name: Alien Pod
description: Short and sweet. Interesting feature with great sidepulls. Big holds the whole way. Gets steeper as you go up.

name: The Bicycle Thief
description: Start on the sculpted features at the bottom and take care negotiating to the second clip. Some of rock is still suspect in this layer. Big reaches will get you to positive sidepulls. Finish on difficult-to-find pockets on the column.

name: Black Bear
description: Start on steep blocks, using big moves on big holds. Crux is on the thin, balancy headwall. Pumpy and technical. Best rock quality at Pointless.

name: Black Betty
description: Short, steep, and powerful. Some cryptic and tenuous movement at the crux from bolts 3 to 5. Eases toward the end. Fun hard route.

name: Disappearing Hat Trick
description: Follow the bolt-line along awkward but positive left-leaning rail.

name: Goat Meal
description: Somewhat overhanging, the crux is firing the big moves over the roof while trying not to blow the delicate feet.

name: Head on a Silver Platypus
description: Start on chossy layer and work over the substantial roof on positive edges. Avoid going left, but trend right on good pinches. The holds thin out but remain positive for a fun, cruising finish.

name: Hoppe Hill
description: A bit tricky, this one. A little overhanging, big moves and smart feet will get you through the crux. Difficult fourth clip.

name: Hungry Eyes
description: Excellent route that is wonderfully sustained at the grade. Vertical climbing on positive edges the whole way up.

name: Hustle and Flow
description: Steep, technical, and hard. Pinches, side pulls, and gastons are the name of the game here. Crux is mid-route.

name: Lords-a-Leaping (formerly 5.7 Crack)
description: Start on first bolt of Black Bear. Pull over small roof on big holds. Scramble up easy 4th class ramp to start of inside corner crack. Don't fall before you place that first piece!  Muchachos y muchachas, the crux of the climb is protected by a bolt. If you fall off the ramp before you get a piece in, you probably shouldn't have been attempting to climb the crack. In other words, it's safe, my babies! PG!

name: Orbit
description: Brilliant route. Start on somewhat powerful pinches, then move into a thin, technical layer. Pull through the short choss layer and finish on fantastic steep blocks. Big moves on positive holds.

name: Rock-in My Sports Bra
description: Easier if you use the crack beginning left of the 3rd bolt, better if you follow the bolt line.

name: Sleepwalker
description: Steep! bouldery start to steep overhang, tricky getting over the ledge and then 5.5 to anchors.

name: Stingray
description: Tallest route before the trail turns around the corner. Slightly overhanging with a difficult finish on tenuous feet.

name: Team Trailer
description: Really fun warm-up despite the significantly chossy start. Lieback and sidepull straight up the crack feature, using positive stemming.

name: What's the Point?
description: Overhung and balancy for the first half. Hidden pockets to pull the roof. Finish on fun finger crack. There is a bolt next to the crack, but it also protects nicely with gear. Bound to be an area classic; this is an excellent route.

name: Angel of Death
description: Start in overhung section to small rest, then use flared crack and thins holds to chains.

name: Bombs Away
description: First bolt is kind of high. Follow groove/crack to slabby face and somewhat runout section to big ledge. Another route that is not a classic.

name: Freakie Stylie
description: Clip stick the first bolt, then climb right leaning, almost horizontal seam/flake to third bolt. Then up through a series of small crimps and end on Fixe sport anchors.    There is a direct vairation to this route that has been done on lead with the first bolt, (which is very high), sticked clipped. Plans are to add a new first bolt lower on the route.

name: Lateralis
description: Hard to read start, to good moves, rest, then main crux going to the chain anchors.

name: My Name Is Mud
description: Another hard-to-read-start followed by some serious slab moves. Gain big flake and mount big ledge at anchors. Definately not a classic but worth doing.

name: Reach for the Sky
description: First route on the right of the Upper RPM Wall. Slabby and hard to read start leads to shallow corner with gaston moves and finishes on diagonal crimps. Chain anchors.

name: Still Life
description: Crux is spread out through the first 3 bolts on slab then backs off to .10+ climbing on fun jugs then crimps. Chain anchors.

name: Sweating Bullets
description: Start up somewhat steep face to crux at 3 bolt, then up to huge rest ledge. Fire the last 4 bolts to the chains via thin face climbing.

name: Chef's Meatballs
description: This route is very sustained and quite a fight for .10d.

name: Don't Forget to Bring a Towel (or Harness)
description: Begin on the start holds of Chef's Meatballs (far right route on the wall) and traverse left crossing Scuzzlebutt, Mr. Hankey, and Ricardo to the end of the traverse at the long grass underneath the start of EDS. Watch for loose rocks, but there are no necessary holds above the first bolt of any route. The route is a grade or two harder when traversing left to right (EDS --> Chef's Meatballs).  Feel free to try it and let me know if I'm completely wrong about the grade. Or, you could just remember to bring your harness and climb the routes with bolts...

name: Drive-by Trucker
description: Sustained and powerful but with good holds. Virtually straight up and slightly overhung until the final few moves.    Bring some lock-off strength and endurance and prepare for a rad time!    Caution - belaying from the log is a good way to catch a choss-bomb right on the dome.

name: EDS
description: Powerful, bouldery route that stay on ya til the chains. Super fun!!

name: Government Shutdown
description: Fun route that starts off with some funky, thuggy moves to the fourth bolt and a decent rest, and then finishes with some fairly easy but techy, sloper moves to the top. Really fun to the sixth bolt but quality diminishes after that.

name: In Between Days
description: Steep start with big moves and some underclings lead to the crux, which involves some big brick pinches to a precise move to a pocket.

name: Mr Hankey
description: This route traverses the low roof in a series of powerful underclings, then plumblines straight for the anchors.

name: Ricardo Gets an Anal Probe
description: Another classic South park route. Powerful from the start to finish.

name: Scuzzlebutt
description: In your face right off the ground. Begins to let up after the fixed draws.     A long and fun trip.

name: Temptation
description: Power endurance route with lots of fun crimps! Pretty steep!

name: Big Gay Al
description: The furthest route to the left.     I haven't done this one; rating info from Matt TeNgaio and Sam Perkins.

name: Cartman
description: Strenuous with very few rests (unless you can find the awesome kneebar).     Great exposure when compared to Smug Alert. Not run out, but a few clips will test your head.

name: Hippy Digger
description: Awesome boulder problem at the bottom with a pumpy finish after the second crux.

name: Make Love Not Warcraft
description: This was once the most technically challenging route at the crag.

name: Scary Rattlesnake
description: A line that very rarely gets climbed.. As of spring '11 it's extremely loose and dangerous.

name: Smug Alert
description: More sustained than Kenny, but with less of a defined crux. A great first SP lead.

name: Who Killed Kenny
description: Great long route with a cryptic crux around a third-height. This is the warm-up, but it's quite stout if you're not used to the area.

name: Alzheimers
description: Just downhill from the gate into TBC, there is a short attractive shallow cream colored corner that leads to small bulge and a few moves up a blunt arête. 5 bolts.  This route has not seen a clean ascent yet.  Thought to be around 12 b or c.  Post a comment with the grade if you send it.

name: Beer Thirty
description: About 30 feet right of the JJ routes, scramble up a loose ramp to the first bolt. Climb up to a thin crack that goes through a small bulge. Continue up to the anchors.

name: Bold in the Bathtub
description: Start in a short, dirty corner and move right. Continue up on easy, blocky rock to a stance just below steeper rock with thin holds.  Stem up to an overhang.  Work up through the roof to a nice corner capped with a small triangular roof.  Stem up and work holds on the right side until you can reach the anchors.

name: Dust in the Wind
description: After clipping the second bolt, make a committing move to a stance below a small bulge.  Find a couple key crimps and move up and left to blocky holds.   Continue up and slightly left to a hueco and a lieback flake.  Make a move hard right and up to a stance.  Pull on to a short headwall  with  good holds but bad feet to a comfortable stance and the anchors.

name: Finger Dance
description: Scramble up to the shelf below the detached pillar. This is the left most route accessed from the shelve below the detached pillar.  Small crimps, thin tips and stemming leads to a small roof. Continue to the anchors on decent but pumpy holds.

name: Ground Zero
description: Starts from the shelf below the detached pillar.  After a couple moves, step up and gain a burly lieback/undercling until you can reach a good horizontal hold. Grab a flake and pull onto a short headwall then move right to the anchors on easy ground.  Shares anchors with Redneck Recycling Center.

name: Heartbreaker
description: Shares the first bolt with JJ1 and then moves left through overhanging rock with a series of big moves until mantling on to a narrow stance.  Easier rock leads to the anchors.

name: In Your Face
description: Boulder up to a shelf and a large ledge.  Continue up a white face to a three foot roof.  Pull the roof into a shallow tan corner and climb to the anchors.

name: JJ Route 1
description: Pull through the overhang on big holds to a cranky move at the lip. Continue up to a crack/corner system and move left to the anchors.

name: JJ Route 2
description: Appears 11+ or 12 something.  Shares first two bolts with JJ1.  After the second bolt, face climb right over the bulge on thin edges and side-pulls.  Finish on independent anchor.  FA thought to be Joel Jackson.

name: One Trick Pony
description: Face climb up brown stone to a ledge. Continue up to a cream colored face right of a short arête. Using the flared slot in the roof, pull through to a stance over the roof.  Pretty much one hard move on what is otherwise a very moderate climb.

name: Pick Your Poison
description: Climb up easy moves to a broken roof band and move up on mostly decent holds.  Continue up until you can work a slighly curving vertical crack.  Make a big reach to a jug and pull your feet up to a stance.  Easier but fun face climbing to the right leads to the anchors.   This is a great route with about 20 feet of continuous pumpy climbing.

name: Pumpster Diving
description: Move up and right until you can pull over a bulge and gain a stance on a sloping shelf.  Crimp up a move or two until you can grab blocky good holds. Work slightly left then pull right to nice looking brown rock with a long flake jammed into a corner. Climb past the hollow flake and continue to the anchors just left of large roof.

name: Redneck Recycling Center
description: Start behind a boulder near the detached pillar and climb through stacked blocks to a broad, smooth face. Crimp up a few moves to gain a corner system. Work up the corner and pull left to the anchors.

name: Runaway
description: Starts just right of Redneck Recycling Center, move up and left to a stance that shares a couple holds with Red Neck Recycling Center.  Then move right to a small roof. Make hard moves through the roof to a short face with a couple more pumpy moves that lead to a ledge and the anchors.  Fun boulder problem crux.

name: Social Distancing
description: Short but powerful.  Boulder up through a big roof and climb a right facing corner.  Easier climbing leads to the top.

name: Velvet Sky
description: Climb the left edge of a brown face to a stance below an obvious arête. Work the arête and corner to a tough pull onto a steep brown face.  Finish with a couple of tough stabs into the correct choice of finger pockets.

name: 2-Fer
description: Starts to the left and shares anchors with DB Goes to TBC.

name: Clay Pigeons
description: Make hard moves off the ground and gain a crack to a stance.  Pull into a crack with on bad feet and move up to the featured roof. Pull the roof and make another hard move to get to the anchors.  Recommended to clip from the rim just above the anchors.

name: DB Goes to TBC
description: Steep climbing leads to an obvious hueco.  A hard pull past the hueco leads to a stance & easier climbing to the anchors.  FA:  Dave Bingham, Nov 2016

name: Ex-Punks (Open Project)
description: Ultra thin crimps over a big roof, suspected 13.  Still waiting a clean ascent.  Comment and leave the grade if you send it.

name: Falling Star
description: Start just right of Lip Service in the grey corner and move right to ledge below an overhanging dihedral. Make a couple of moves up the corner until you can jam the crack to the top.

name: Get Down to Get Up
description: Mirror image climb of Thumper. Move up to the big corner and traverse right under the big roof until you can pull around the roof to a stance. Continue up to the anchors.

name: Godzilla
description: Work up to a big roof through very steep terrain on widely spaced but decent holds.  Wrestle though the weakness in the roof to a huge ledge.  A few move easy moves lead to the anchors.

name: Heavy Metal Thunder
description: Likely an old Joel Jackson route.  Bolt added down low and the anchor was moved (the old anchor is in a block on the ground now!).  Climb up a nice looking corner system to anchors below a large tree on the rim.

name: In the Line of Fire
description: Climb up a left facing corner to a ledge below an arête.  Climb either side of the arête to the anchors.

name: It's Getting Better All the Time
description: Make an awkward move into a sandy left facing corner.  Step right to a stance.  Move more or less straight up steep, excellent quality rock on crimps and pockets.  Keep moving up steep terrain until it backs off at the anchors.

name: Justified
